1
00:01:17,188 --> 00:01:18,896
DEAR, HOW ABOUT ONE OF THESE GIRLS?

2
00:02:41,896 --> 00:02:44,563
DO DEEWANE SEHER MEIN

3
00:03:06,355 --> 00:03:09,646
Shashank, good morning.

4
00:03:11,355 --> 00:03:13,105
All the best.

5
00:03:49,355 --> 00:03:51,230
<i>Shashank, where the heck are you?</i>

6
00:03:51,355 --> 00:03:54,688
"Manis", I'm at the hospital.
My grandma's really serious.

7
00:03:54,771 --> 00:03:55,938
<i>Well, I'm serious too.</i>

8
00:03:56,021 --> 00:03:58,688
<i>The Seoul team is online.</i>
<i>The client's asking where you are.</i>

9
00:03:58,771 --> 00:04:00,855
I sent you the docket already.

10
00:04:01,021 --> 00:04:02,771
You'll have to present it.
I can't make it.

11
00:04:02,855 --> 00:04:06,063
<i>Wait, me? It's your presentation.</i>
<i>You'll have to do it.</i>

12
00:04:06,146 --> 00:04:08,146
<i>How am I supposed to pull that off?</i>
<i>You just sent the email…</i>

13
00:04:08,230 --> 00:04:09,896
Dr. Dheeraj, did the MRI report come in?

14
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:11,938
- <i>Shashank, listen…</i>
- Hold on, "Manis".

15
00:04:14,855 --> 00:04:17,563
Sir, should I get you some water
or just hook up an IV?

16
00:04:38,105 --> 00:04:41,105
So, can you cook?

17
00:04:46,146 --> 00:04:47,313
Can you?

18
00:04:47,396 --> 00:04:49,646
Who, me?

19
00:04:49,730 --> 00:04:51,146
I can make Maggie.

20
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,480
Wow.

21
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:55,771
I'll settle for Maggie, then.

22
00:04:56,938 --> 00:04:58,396
Nice sense of humor.

23
00:04:58,938 --> 00:05:02,563
Have you ever thought
about getting contact lenses?

24
00:05:02,646 --> 00:05:03,605
Of course.

25
00:05:03,688 --> 00:05:04,855
I gave it some thought

26
00:05:04,938 --> 00:05:07,730
and decided I don't want them.

27
00:05:07,980 --> 00:05:09,271
- Really?
- Yes.

28
00:05:09,355 --> 00:05:12,521
But I think contact lenses
are way better…

29
00:05:12,688 --> 00:05:14,521
especially for girls.

30
00:05:14,646 --> 00:05:15,646
Right?

31
00:05:17,521 --> 00:05:19,855
Did you ever consider
getting a brain implant?

32
00:05:20,271 --> 00:05:23,438
A brain implant is far better
than having no brain at all. Yeah?

33
00:05:26,646 --> 00:05:28,271
I didn't mean that. I mean…

34
00:05:28,896 --> 00:05:29,896
Nice milkshake.

35
00:05:31,688 --> 00:05:32,521
Thank you.

36
00:05:34,063 --> 00:05:35,813
Hey, just…

37
00:05:49,271 --> 00:05:52,355
- Mom, pass me a <i>roti</i>. Just one.
- Okay.

38
00:05:53,355 --> 00:05:54,938
- Here you go.
- Pumpkin?

39
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:57,105
Come on, dear. Dinner's ready.

40
00:05:57,230 --> 00:05:59,646
<i>They are ugly</i>
<i>and they have a peculiar gait.</i>

41
00:05:59,813 --> 00:06:01,563
<i>They laugh in a strange way.</i>

42
00:06:03,063 --> 00:06:04,938
- Yogurt dip?
- If chaos counts.

43
00:06:05,063 --> 00:06:06,146
What's in it?

44
00:06:06,230 --> 00:06:07,146
Cucumber.

45
00:06:07,688 --> 00:06:09,896
Alright, I'll have a little.

46
00:06:10,355 --> 00:06:12,730
- Come, Roshni.
- Come on, dear.

47
00:06:12,813 --> 00:06:14,188
It's your favorite dish.

48
00:06:14,271 --> 00:06:16,355
Pumpkin can't be anyone's favorite, Dad.

49
00:06:16,813 --> 00:06:17,688
Thanks.

50
00:06:18,146 --> 00:06:19,646
I'll manage something.

51
00:06:19,813 --> 00:06:21,355
"I'll settle for Maggie, then."

52
00:06:21,855 --> 00:06:23,771
You should've just said you can cook.

53
00:06:23,855 --> 00:06:25,105
I would've taught you.

54
00:06:27,355 --> 00:06:28,230
Forget it.

55
00:06:28,355 --> 00:06:30,438
The guy looked
like a total asshole in his photo.

56
00:06:30,521 --> 00:06:31,771
- What?
- What did he look like?

57
00:06:31,855 --> 00:06:34,188
An asshole! The kind
you can't expect anything from,

58
00:06:34,271 --> 00:06:36,563
and has a tiny hole
where the brain's supposed to be.

59
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:38,396
Bittu told me that's what it means.

60
00:06:40,646 --> 00:06:44,980
Well, he didn't just
look like an asshole, he was one.

61
00:06:45,938 --> 00:06:49,938
Dear, if an asshole
makes six lakhs a month,

62
00:06:50,021 --> 00:06:51,730
we don't call him an asshole.

63
00:06:51,813 --> 00:06:54,980
How many times have I told you
to try the dating apps?

64
00:06:55,146 --> 00:06:56,688
She just keeps spending money
on coffee dates.

65
00:06:56,771 --> 00:06:57,771
So what?

66
00:06:57,855 --> 00:06:58,855
Should I get married
just for the heck of it?

67
00:06:58,938 --> 00:07:02,563
Yes. In this country,
most people do exactly that.

68
00:07:02,646 --> 00:07:05,855
For the first time you've actually
said something sensible.

69
00:07:05,980 --> 00:07:08,230
Is it necessary
to nag her every single day?

70
00:07:08,313 --> 00:07:09,771
Yes. It's necessary.

71
00:07:09,855 --> 00:07:11,855
Look at Naina. She's so pretty

72
00:07:11,938 --> 00:07:13,438
but it took us forever
to find her a groom--

73
00:07:13,521 --> 00:07:16,021
If you put your energy into cooking

74
00:07:16,105 --> 00:07:18,105
instead of this nonsense,

75
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:20,438
maybe we wouldn't be stuck
eating this boring dish every morning.

76
00:07:20,521 --> 00:07:21,688
And last night's leftover curry.

77
00:07:21,771 --> 00:07:23,521
And last year's yogurt dip.

78
00:07:23,813 --> 00:07:24,980
Are we out of eggs?

79
00:07:25,230 --> 00:07:26,605
You'll be out of them soon.

80
00:07:27,146 --> 00:07:30,438
If you keep up this drama,
you'll hit menopause before you know it.

81
00:07:30,688 --> 00:07:32,230
- What?
- Nothing.

82
00:07:32,313 --> 00:07:34,438
How can she get there
when I still haven't?

83
00:07:34,521 --> 00:07:35,646
Wait, you haven't?

84
00:07:35,771 --> 00:07:36,605
Have you?

85
00:07:36,688 --> 00:07:38,355
Guys, enough! That's it!

86
00:07:38,563 --> 00:07:41,438
I can't keep meeting idiots
and having my day ruined.

87
00:07:41,521 --> 00:07:43,563
If you have a problem with that, then…

88
00:07:43,688 --> 00:07:44,521
Then?

89
00:07:44,605 --> 00:07:45,980
- Then?
- Then?

90
00:07:48,021 --> 00:07:48,980
Then…

91
00:07:49,771 --> 00:07:51,146
I'll just leave this house.

92
00:07:52,063 --> 00:07:54,563
- Have your dinner, dear.
- I'll order it on online.

93
00:07:54,646 --> 00:07:57,355
Wow! Very good! Lovely!

94
00:07:57,521 --> 00:07:59,855
Are you happy now?
You totally ruined the mood.

95
00:08:05,855 --> 00:08:09,646
{\an8}NAINA: HEY, ROSH!
WANT TO GO FOR SUNDAY BRUNCH?

96
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:12,563
ROSHNI: YES! JUST TELL ME WHERE…

97
00:08:24,230 --> 00:08:26,438
ANIL: MEETING STARTED. BRO, WHERE ARE YOU?

98
00:08:31,021 --> 00:08:32,855
No, the chart looks good.

99
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:35,146
Do you have anything
on consumer preference?

100
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:41,813
Shashank, come.

101
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:43,521
Sit down.

102
00:08:58,771 --> 00:09:00,563
So, Shashank…

103
00:09:01,521 --> 00:09:02,563
Yes, sir?

104
00:09:03,813 --> 00:09:06,730
Yesterday you came in at 9:30.

105
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:08,438
Logged in at 10.

106
00:09:09,355 --> 00:09:10,438
Had tea at 10:30.

107
00:09:10,521 --> 00:09:14,021
And by 11:30, you left.

108
00:09:14,521 --> 00:09:18,980
You knew we had a crucial meeting at 12.

109
00:09:19,771 --> 00:09:20,896
Why?

110
00:09:25,105 --> 00:09:26,396
Sir, I'd informed "Manis".

111
00:09:26,521 --> 00:09:29,521
- I'd kept him updated…
- Stop hiding behind Manish.

112
00:09:29,688 --> 00:09:31,855
You weren't in the meeting,

113
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:33,730
and I want to know why.

114
00:09:34,146 --> 00:09:35,521
What's going on?

115
00:09:36,771 --> 00:09:38,688
Sir, actually, it's my grandma.

116
00:09:38,813 --> 00:09:39,771
Grandma?

117
00:09:39,855 --> 00:09:40,980
Grandma…

118
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:42,521
She's quite old, sir.

119
00:09:44,521 --> 00:09:45,605
She was aged, so…

120
00:09:45,688 --> 00:09:47,771
- She was?
- She is alive.

121
00:09:47,855 --> 00:09:49,355
- She is alive.
- I see.

122
00:09:49,438 --> 00:09:52,813
It's serious. She's in the ICU.
She's critical, sir.

123
00:09:52,896 --> 00:09:54,771
I'm her grandson, so I…

124
00:09:54,855 --> 00:09:56,980
No, of course. I get it.

125
00:09:57,105 --> 00:09:58,855
- Anil?
- Sir, they're really close.

126
00:09:58,938 --> 00:10:00,896
You should've told me
if you knew about it.

127
00:10:00,980 --> 00:10:02,855
I'm sitting here, getting mad at him.

128
00:10:03,021 --> 00:10:04,021
Sorry, sir.

129
00:10:04,313 --> 00:10:05,313
What happened?

130
00:10:06,855 --> 00:10:08,355
Something serious?

131
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:09,980
Yes, sir.

132
00:10:10,230 --> 00:10:11,855
- What's wrong?
- Very serious.

133
00:10:12,730 --> 00:10:13,563
What is it?

134
00:10:13,646 --> 00:10:15,813
I don't know how to explain it.

135
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:17,313
Tell him.

136
00:10:17,396 --> 00:10:19,355
Anil, you knew?
Why didn't you say something?

137
00:10:19,438 --> 00:10:21,105
I just found out…

138
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:24,105
Even I was shocked
when I got to know about it.

139
00:10:24,438 --> 00:10:26,230
It's a bit personal. Tell him.
He'll hear you out.

140
00:10:26,313 --> 00:10:27,230
Sir, if you could…

141
00:10:27,313 --> 00:10:28,396
Sir, please.

142
00:10:28,521 --> 00:10:29,438
What happened?

143
00:10:29,521 --> 00:10:31,188
What do I say, sir?

144
00:10:32,313 --> 00:10:33,813
Sir, my grandma

145
00:10:34,813 --> 00:10:37,646
has fibromyalgia of the intestinal cavity.

146
00:10:40,438 --> 00:10:41,688
That's very serious.

147
00:10:41,771 --> 00:10:43,980
No really, that's quite serious.

148
00:10:46,355 --> 00:10:48,355
If you need anything, just let me know.

149
00:10:48,438 --> 00:10:50,188
- Don't worry.
- Yes, sir.

150
00:10:54,105 --> 00:10:55,563
- Anil.
- Yes?

151
00:10:55,646 --> 00:10:57,355
Present the financial report…

152
00:10:57,438 --> 00:11:01,646
So, sir, the 10 percent rise we saw
was from Southern Asia…

153
00:11:03,938 --> 00:11:04,771
Thank you, sir.

154
00:11:04,855 --> 00:11:05,813
Shashank.

155
00:11:06,813 --> 00:11:08,355
Your grandma will be alright.

156
00:11:08,521 --> 00:11:10,313
Don't stress, okay?

157
00:11:10,521 --> 00:11:11,980
- Yes, sir.
- Bye.

158
00:11:16,355 --> 00:11:18,355
Do you have any shame left at all?

159
00:11:18,521 --> 00:11:21,521
Your grandma must be
turning in her grave. Get it?

160
00:11:21,605 --> 00:11:22,855
Let's just go.

161
00:11:23,146 --> 00:11:25,771
And what the hell is fibromyalgia
of the intestinal cavity?

162
00:11:25,855 --> 00:11:27,438
You get cavities in your teeth.

163
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:29,355
And you shoved one into her intestines?

164
00:11:29,438 --> 00:11:31,605
Why do you keep putting your grandma
in the ICU so often?

165
00:11:31,688 --> 00:11:33,813
Even doctors don't visit
that place as much.

166
00:11:33,938 --> 00:11:35,855
That's the best part about my grandma.

167
00:11:35,938 --> 00:11:37,521
She's always been there for me.

168
00:11:37,605 --> 00:11:40,313
In life and in the afterlife.

169
00:11:41,521 --> 00:11:44,355
You and your nonstop nonsense.

170
00:11:44,438 --> 00:11:46,771
Why do you freeze up in front of the boss?

171
00:11:46,855 --> 00:11:47,855
What do I even say?

172
00:11:47,938 --> 00:11:49,938
Every word has an 's' in it.

173
00:11:50,021 --> 00:11:52,355
"Presentason", "finansial",
"wasing" machine…

174
00:11:52,521 --> 00:11:53,980
Good morning, sir.

175
00:11:54,105 --> 00:11:56,146
- What have you got for lunch?
- <i>Chicken Biryani.</i>

176
00:11:56,230 --> 00:11:57,563
I'm vegetarian.

177
00:11:57,646 --> 00:11:59,355
Forget the <i>biryani</i>. Here you go.

178
00:11:59,438 --> 00:12:00,521
Sorry, sir.

179
00:12:00,855 --> 00:12:01,771
Good.

180
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,563
Come on, man.

181
00:12:04,355 --> 00:12:05,980
Just speak up a little.

182
00:12:06,105 --> 00:12:07,646
It won't kill you.

183
00:12:07,771 --> 00:12:10,355
It'll actually help you and not me.

184
00:12:10,855 --> 00:12:13,230
You always speak for me.
It's all the same.

185
00:12:13,813 --> 00:12:15,355
No, it's not the same.

186
00:12:15,438 --> 00:12:17,730
If I speak up, I'll get promoted.
You won't.

187
00:12:17,813 --> 00:12:19,855
I'll get a salary hike. You won't.

188
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:22,271
You're a nice guy,
they'll chew you up and spit you out.

189
00:12:22,355 --> 00:12:23,521
Try to understand.

190
00:12:24,230 --> 00:12:25,771
Speak and you will get it.

191
00:12:25,855 --> 00:12:26,771
What?

192
00:12:27,355 --> 00:12:29,813
If you just speak up,
you'll get what you deserve.

193
00:12:30,063 --> 00:12:32,730
What do I do?
This is how I've been since I was a kid.

194
00:12:39,355 --> 00:12:40,271
Hold that pose.

195
00:12:40,980 --> 00:12:42,563
Yeah, wait. I'll let you…

196
00:12:42,646 --> 00:12:44,313
- Listen, mail it to me.
- I can send it.

197
00:12:44,396 --> 00:12:46,271
No, I'll handle it. Don't you worry.

198
00:12:46,355 --> 00:12:47,730
- You sure?
- Just send it to me.

199
00:12:47,813 --> 00:12:49,271
- Hold on, my sister's calling.
- Yeah.

200
00:12:49,355 --> 00:12:50,521
Hello?

201
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:52,146
Hey. Where are you?

202
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:53,355
I'm here.

203
00:12:53,646 --> 00:12:56,563
- Walk straight ahead. Can you see me?
- Yeah, I can see you.

204
00:12:57,646 --> 00:12:58,730
Yeah.

205
00:13:03,521 --> 00:13:05,980
Wow! Cool vibes in here.

206
00:13:06,063 --> 00:13:08,021
Is this an office or some kind of club?

207
00:13:08,313 --> 00:13:11,438
I'm here working on a weekend,
and you're soaking up the vibes?

208
00:13:13,521 --> 00:13:15,271
Almost done. Five minutes.

209
00:13:15,355 --> 00:13:17,105
Rosh, we planned brunch

210
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:18,521
but now it's lunchtime.

211
00:13:18,646 --> 00:13:21,521
- I know, I'm sorry. Just the deadline…
- I'm on…

212
00:13:21,688 --> 00:13:23,896
Yes. I got it.

213
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:26,771
I wish I had her body.

214
00:13:26,855 --> 00:13:28,480
What exactly would that change?

215
00:13:28,563 --> 00:13:29,480
Tell me.

216
00:13:29,688 --> 00:13:31,688
Relax. What would've happened anyway?

217
00:13:31,813 --> 00:13:34,021
I'd just get a few more likes
on social media and maybe,

218
00:13:34,105 --> 00:13:35,896
Arjun would drop in a compliment.

219
00:13:35,980 --> 00:13:37,105
- Arjun!
- That's it.

220
00:13:37,271 --> 00:13:40,105
If Arjun hadn't gone to Delhi,
you wouldn't be meeting me.

221
00:13:40,188 --> 00:13:41,230
I know it.

222
00:13:41,855 --> 00:13:43,438
- Rosh…
- Yeah, I'm just finishing.

223
00:13:43,521 --> 00:13:44,855
- Hi!
- Hi!

224
00:13:44,980 --> 00:13:46,188
She's here for?

225
00:13:46,271 --> 00:13:47,563
This is my boss, Mandy.

226
00:13:47,646 --> 00:13:49,355
And my sister, Naina.

227
00:13:49,521 --> 00:13:51,771
- Hi!
- Oh, you mean cousin?

228
00:13:51,938 --> 00:13:54,563
- No. Sisters.
- Sisters!

229
00:13:54,688 --> 00:13:57,563
She's older, a bit richer,
and way prettier.

230
00:13:57,646 --> 00:14:00,188
- Shut up! That's silly!
- I didn't mean it like that.

231
00:14:00,271 --> 00:14:01,771
- She's being silly.
- Yeah. Okay.

232
00:14:01,855 --> 00:14:03,980
- Well, lovely meeting you then.
- Same here.

233
00:14:04,105 --> 00:14:05,896
And I agree with you.
She's simply gorgeous.

234
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:07,146
- Thank you.
- Have a great day.

235
00:14:07,230 --> 00:14:08,230
You too.

236
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,938
I keep telling you to change.

237
00:14:15,021 --> 00:14:17,938
- Oh, please!
- You're always eating junk.

238
00:14:18,021 --> 00:14:19,605
It's loaded with fat, Rosh.

239
00:14:19,688 --> 00:14:22,021
- Don't eat it. It's bad for your skin too.
- You know what?

240
00:14:22,105 --> 00:14:24,771
- Have some. It'll make you happy.
- I'm very happy, Rosh. Let's go.

241
00:14:24,855 --> 00:14:26,063
I'm almost done…

242
00:14:26,146 --> 00:14:27,605
- What's so special about it?
- Let's go.

243
00:14:27,688 --> 00:14:29,063
I'll just freshen up. Two minutes.

244
00:14:29,146 --> 00:14:30,438
Hurry up, Rosh.

245
00:14:30,563 --> 00:14:31,896
Coming!

246
00:15:12,438 --> 00:15:13,771
You're living a tough life!

247
00:15:13,855 --> 00:15:17,313
Mandy's breathing down your neck
at the office, and at home, it's mom.

248
00:15:18,355 --> 00:15:19,355
You saw?

249
00:15:20,021 --> 00:15:21,105
Nice, no?

250
00:15:21,230 --> 00:15:22,438
Summer nails.

251
00:15:23,146 --> 00:15:24,355
Very nice.

252
00:15:24,980 --> 00:15:28,105
You should get yours done too.
Honestly, your nails look rough.

253
00:15:29,230 --> 00:15:30,521
Don't you get bored?

254
00:15:31,355 --> 00:15:33,355
Try switching it up once in a while.

255
00:15:33,563 --> 00:15:35,105
Change your hairstyle.

256
00:15:35,230 --> 00:15:37,438
When was the last time you had a facial?

257
00:15:37,771 --> 00:15:39,105
Do something.

258
00:15:43,230 --> 00:15:46,146
So that Mandy stops assuming
we're cousins and not sisters?

259
00:15:47,021 --> 00:15:48,771
Rubbish. Mandy is stupid.

260
00:15:48,855 --> 00:15:49,813
Please.

261
00:15:50,355 --> 00:15:52,938
What's wrong with grooming
yourself, looking good?

262
00:15:53,646 --> 00:15:55,105
I have tried, okay?

263
00:15:55,188 --> 00:15:56,438
Look where that got me.

264
00:15:56,646 --> 00:15:58,521
Even after everything, Sahil just…

265
00:15:58,980 --> 00:16:00,896
You're really still hung up on Sahil?

266
00:16:01,271 --> 00:16:04,355
Listen. Firstly, Sahil was an ass. Okay?

267
00:16:04,813 --> 00:16:07,021
Thank God, you saw it
before it went too far.

268
00:16:07,146 --> 00:16:08,855
It's his loss, not yours.

269
00:16:08,980 --> 00:16:11,105
Stop pestering me and just eat your salad!

270
00:16:11,188 --> 00:16:12,730
I'm just talking to you, Rosh.

271
00:16:12,855 --> 00:16:13,688
You…

272
00:16:13,855 --> 00:16:15,021
I'll force-feed you pasta
if you keep at it.

273
00:16:15,105 --> 00:16:17,563
- I'll shove the salad right back.
- I'm allergic to salad.

274
00:16:17,646 --> 00:16:19,396
- And I'm allergic to pasta.
- You…

275
00:16:19,771 --> 00:16:20,855
Cheers.

276
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:22,646
Cheers.

277
00:16:24,563 --> 00:16:29,105
<i>We will meet on unfamiliar paths</i>

278
00:16:29,646 --> 00:16:34,146
<i>We will meet…</i>

279
00:16:35,063 --> 00:16:36,438
Listen.

280
00:16:37,355 --> 00:16:39,438
Why don't you buy a car of your own?

281
00:16:39,521 --> 00:16:42,063
How long will you keep
hopping in and out of taxis?

282
00:16:42,563 --> 00:16:44,355
I don't need a car, Dad.

283
00:16:44,563 --> 00:16:45,563
Really?

284
00:16:47,980 --> 00:16:49,646
Then what do you need?

285
00:16:51,855 --> 00:16:55,896
You don't need a car,
you don't need a house…

286
00:16:56,646 --> 00:16:59,188
- Do you even need us--
- Take the next right.

287
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:08,355
What's this?

288
00:17:09,105 --> 00:17:10,230
The list.

289
00:17:10,355 --> 00:17:12,980
The one you always forget to mention.

290
00:17:14,271 --> 00:17:16,980
We have a big house in Patna.

291
00:17:17,271 --> 00:17:20,146
Your uncle's an IIT graduate.

292
00:17:20,688 --> 00:17:23,646
You almost got into IIM.

293
00:17:24,355 --> 00:17:26,688
Forget it, we'll handle all this.

294
00:17:26,771 --> 00:17:31,688
Just don't forget to say
your salary's in six figures.

295
00:17:31,771 --> 00:17:32,980
Okay?

296
00:17:35,563 --> 00:17:37,230
Okay, Dad.

297
00:17:39,271 --> 00:17:40,521
Hello?

298
00:17:41,813 --> 00:17:43,396
Don't get nervous, Son.

299
00:17:43,521 --> 00:17:44,855
Just speak honestly.

300
00:17:45,563 --> 00:17:49,605
Let her see who you really are.
She should know you're a sweet boy.

301
00:17:50,438 --> 00:17:53,980
Why didn't you check while choosing dad
if he's a sweet boy too?

302
00:17:54,230 --> 00:17:56,438
No one asked me what I thought.

303
00:17:57,771 --> 00:17:59,730
- Shall I fix your hair?
- No, it's fine.

304
00:17:59,813 --> 00:18:02,355
- They're sticking up at the back.
- That's the style.

305
00:18:04,646 --> 00:18:06,646
We visited Mumbai ten years ago.

306
00:18:06,771 --> 00:18:09,938
The roads are still the same,
full of potholes.

307
00:18:10,021 --> 00:18:12,146
- True.
- But there are new flyovers now.

308
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:14,146
The sea link is close to our place.

309
00:18:14,230 --> 00:18:16,230
- Do you have a sea link there?
- No, we--

310
00:18:16,313 --> 00:18:18,563
Right. You don't have the sea nearby.

311
00:18:18,938 --> 00:18:21,646
Shashank's a proper Mumbai boy now.

312
00:18:21,771 --> 00:18:23,480
He says, "Mumbai's got the vibes."

313
00:18:23,563 --> 00:18:24,396
What's that?

314
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:26,771
Back in our day,
we didn't have those vibes.

315
00:18:26,855 --> 00:18:28,980
What is that supposed to mean, anyway?

316
00:18:29,355 --> 00:18:32,771
- So, you're settled in Patna?
- Yes.

317
00:18:32,855 --> 00:18:34,980
We've got a big house there.

318
00:18:35,105 --> 00:18:37,188
- Where else would we go, really?
- Exactly.

319
00:18:37,271 --> 00:18:38,771
You should visit us sometime.

320
00:18:38,855 --> 00:18:41,480
Every room is air-conditioned.
You'll be comfortable.

321
00:18:41,563 --> 00:18:43,771
- The whole family's there now.
- I see.

322
00:18:43,855 --> 00:18:46,646
Shashank's uncle
is an IIT Mumbai graduate.

323
00:18:46,730 --> 00:18:47,563
Wow!

324
00:18:47,646 --> 00:18:49,646
But even he chose to stay back.

325
00:18:49,771 --> 00:18:53,271
These days, IIT and IIM
aren't that uncommon anymore.

326
00:18:53,355 --> 00:18:54,230
Yes, true.

327
00:18:54,355 --> 00:18:55,771
There is IIT in Mumbai too.

328
00:18:55,855 --> 00:18:56,896
Please have some snacks.

329
00:18:56,980 --> 00:18:59,980
Shashank missed IIM by just one mark.

330
00:19:00,105 --> 00:19:01,021
One mark?

331
00:19:01,146 --> 00:19:03,105
- Of course!
- Two marks.

332
00:19:03,230 --> 00:19:05,355
- No. One mark.
- It happens.

333
00:19:05,521 --> 00:19:06,646
No problem.

334
00:19:09,646 --> 00:19:11,271
Roshni! Come in, dear.

335
00:19:11,355 --> 00:19:12,355
Come, sit.

336
00:19:12,438 --> 00:19:13,438
Greet everyone.

337
00:19:13,521 --> 00:19:14,563
- Have a seat.
- Sit down.

338
00:19:14,646 --> 00:19:16,105
- Hi.
- Join us.

339
00:19:16,521 --> 00:19:18,646
- Come on.
- Hello.

340
00:19:18,771 --> 00:19:20,646
- Hello.
- Have a seat.

341
00:19:21,813 --> 00:19:24,021
You told me
our family friends were visiting.

342
00:19:32,521 --> 00:19:34,938
So, Roshni, what do you do?

343
00:19:35,105 --> 00:19:37,938
I'm a content creator.
Mostly fashion and beauty--

344
00:19:38,021 --> 00:19:39,980
Well, she topped
her Mass Communication course.

345
00:19:40,063 --> 00:19:41,438
She's a really good writer.

346
00:19:41,521 --> 00:19:44,771
She gets over a million likes
on all her articles.

347
00:19:44,855 --> 00:19:46,771
- Tell them, dear.
- You just told them.

348
00:19:46,855 --> 00:19:49,605
Her English is excellent.

349
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:51,188
She doesn't like Hindi movies.

350
00:19:51,271 --> 00:19:54,355
Her favorite actors include
Tom Cruise, Bill Gates, you know.

351
00:19:54,813 --> 00:19:55,688
Right?

352
00:20:03,146 --> 00:20:05,605
Kids, why are you sitting here
with us older folk?

353
00:20:06,271 --> 00:20:08,980
Take a walk and talk in private.

354
00:20:09,146 --> 00:20:10,855
You'll get bored here.

355
00:20:11,313 --> 00:20:12,438
Take him.

356
00:20:14,646 --> 00:20:15,646
Let's go.

357
00:20:38,646 --> 00:20:40,396
- Shall we sit over there?
- Yes.

358
00:20:48,688 --> 00:20:51,396
You are here to see me, right?
Go on, take a good look.

359
00:20:54,771 --> 00:20:55,688
Done?

360
00:20:56,063 --> 00:20:57,021
Can we go back now?

361
00:20:57,105 --> 00:20:58,021
Wait.

362
00:20:58,855 --> 00:20:59,771
My turn now.

363
00:21:10,646 --> 00:21:12,771
I can't cook.

364
00:21:13,521 --> 00:21:14,563
Well, I can.

365
00:21:14,646 --> 00:21:16,646
Thai, Chinese, Italian, you name it.

366
00:21:16,730 --> 00:21:18,605
I actually like South Indian food.

367
00:21:19,105 --> 00:21:22,605
<i>Plain-dosa, Masala-dosa,</i>
<i>Appam, Uttapam, Idli…</i>

368
00:21:22,771 --> 00:21:23,813
I can make them all.

369
00:21:24,938 --> 00:21:26,021
Even the <i>Rasam</i>…

370
00:21:26,771 --> 00:21:27,980
I mean, I swear on you.

371
00:21:56,563 --> 00:21:58,980
By the way,
are those prescription glasses?

372
00:21:59,063 --> 00:22:01,438
Does anyone wear glasses
without a prescription?

373
00:22:01,521 --> 00:22:02,521
Right.

374
00:22:05,230 --> 00:22:06,688
So, would you be okay…

375
00:22:07,438 --> 00:22:10,313
with someone who needs glasses?

376
00:22:10,521 --> 00:22:11,605
I'm okay.

377
00:22:12,146 --> 00:22:15,146
I don't mind it.

378
00:22:21,855 --> 00:22:23,688
Nice weather today.

379
00:22:24,938 --> 00:22:27,271
- Looks like it's about to rain.
- I know.

380
00:22:27,646 --> 00:22:28,896
You like the rain?

381
00:22:30,355 --> 00:22:33,813
For me, rain just means humidity,

382
00:22:33,980 --> 00:22:36,563
waterlogged roads, and soggy clothes.

383
00:22:37,355 --> 00:22:38,521
Right.

384
00:22:39,021 --> 00:22:42,230
For me, it's ginger tea

385
00:22:42,855 --> 00:22:44,646
and old romantic songs.

386
00:22:45,230 --> 00:22:48,021
<i>Raindrops fall softly in the monsoon</i>

387
00:22:48,105 --> 00:22:50,980
You clearly have too much free time.

388
00:22:58,521 --> 00:22:59,771
Do you like your job?

389
00:23:01,646 --> 00:23:04,813
Selling electronic appliances
isn't exactly thrilling.

390
00:23:05,688 --> 00:23:06,771
But it's okay.

391
00:23:08,105 --> 00:23:10,021
What do you sell, exactly?

392
00:23:12,521 --> 00:23:13,521
I…

393
00:23:14,105 --> 00:23:15,271
Well…

394
00:23:16,521 --> 00:23:18,230
"Wasing" machines…

395
00:23:19,688 --> 00:23:21,063
Wow!

396
00:23:21,730 --> 00:23:23,438
Did you make these snacks at home?

397
00:23:23,521 --> 00:23:26,438
No, there's a shop nearby.
They serve amazing food.

398
00:23:26,521 --> 00:23:28,313
Well, we've made sandwiches at home.

399
00:23:28,396 --> 00:23:29,771
- She made them.
- Mom, please…

400
00:23:29,855 --> 00:23:32,563
- You don't make them at home?
- She does.

401
00:23:32,646 --> 00:23:35,605
We get everything easily around here,
so there's no need to cook much.

402
00:23:35,688 --> 00:23:38,646
- You must've taught Roshni, right?
- She can cook everything.

403
00:23:44,813 --> 00:23:47,188
So what do you do
when you're in a bad mood?

404
00:23:48,771 --> 00:23:49,813
I eat.

405
00:23:50,813 --> 00:23:51,813
You?

406
00:23:52,271 --> 00:23:53,480
I cook.

407
00:24:00,771 --> 00:24:02,021
Excuse me.

408
00:24:05,230 --> 00:24:06,146
Yes!

409
00:24:07,146 --> 00:24:08,230
What happened?

410
00:24:08,771 --> 00:24:11,438
I won first prize
in a street photography contest.

411
00:24:11,521 --> 00:24:12,438
A microwave.

412
00:24:12,521 --> 00:24:13,646
- Oh.
- Yes.

413
00:24:13,771 --> 00:24:15,646
Street photography contest, huh?

414
00:24:15,771 --> 00:24:17,521
Yeah, I often participate
in such contests.

415
00:24:17,605 --> 00:24:21,313
I've won a phone, a TV, an air fryer,
which I gave to mom…

416
00:24:21,438 --> 00:24:22,646
and now a microwave.

417
00:24:22,771 --> 00:24:26,146
Wow! I've never won a contest.

418
00:24:41,105 --> 00:24:43,771
So, what kind of a girl
are you looking for?

419
00:24:45,021 --> 00:24:46,563
I mean, do you have a list?

420
00:24:47,230 --> 00:24:49,230
A list? I'm not out grocery shopping.

421
00:24:49,813 --> 00:24:52,855
I just want someone
who feels like home.

422
00:24:53,188 --> 00:24:55,480
And if I keep winning contests
along the way…

423
00:24:55,563 --> 00:24:58,105
I mean, someone like you.

424
00:25:01,521 --> 00:25:02,646
Someone like you.

425
00:25:02,771 --> 00:25:04,146
It's going to rain.

426
00:25:04,230 --> 00:25:05,355
Let's head downstairs.

427
00:25:06,521 --> 00:25:08,063
Should we take the clothes off?

428
00:25:09,063 --> 00:25:10,063
What?

429
00:25:11,105 --> 00:25:12,521
The ones hanging over there.

430
00:25:12,855 --> 00:25:14,771
- They'll get soaked otherwise.
- Yeah.

431
00:26:04,646 --> 00:26:06,271
Hey, you guys are back!

432
00:26:08,521 --> 00:26:09,688
Why did you bother?

433
00:26:09,771 --> 00:26:11,271
Hand them over. Let it be.

434
00:26:11,355 --> 00:26:12,605
I've got them.

435
00:26:16,438 --> 00:26:19,230
Alright, Shashank has agreed.

436
00:26:19,855 --> 00:26:22,146
It's time to talk about what comes next.

437
00:26:22,230 --> 00:26:25,605
But first, let me offer you some sweets.
Here you go.

438
00:26:25,688 --> 00:26:27,271
Of course, as you say.

439
00:26:27,355 --> 00:26:30,355
I think we should have
the engagement within a week,

440
00:26:30,521 --> 00:26:32,646
and plan the wedding for January.

441
00:26:35,438 --> 00:26:36,980
Can we ask Roshni too?

442
00:26:37,105 --> 00:26:39,271
Roshni, can you come here for a minute?

443
00:26:39,355 --> 00:26:40,438
Come here.

444
00:26:41,438 --> 00:26:44,688
Is there anything
you'd like to say or ask?

445
00:26:47,021 --> 00:26:48,688
Please don't hesitate.

446
00:26:50,438 --> 00:26:51,688
I…

447
00:26:53,313 --> 00:26:54,855
I don't want to get married.

448
00:27:02,355 --> 00:27:04,021
You should've folded the clothes.

449
00:27:04,771 --> 00:27:07,021
Maybe even ironed them.

450
00:27:09,355 --> 00:27:12,438
You already have a PhD
in household chores.

451
00:27:14,105 --> 00:27:16,563
He is the son
of Patna's most well-known builder.

452
00:27:16,646 --> 00:27:18,646
Please stop it.

453
00:27:19,813 --> 00:27:21,855
He's already in a bad mood.

454
00:27:23,105 --> 00:27:25,813
Son, it's possible

455
00:27:26,146 --> 00:27:28,146
that she has a boyfriend.

456
00:27:28,688 --> 00:27:29,688
Wow, Mom.

457
00:27:29,771 --> 00:27:31,438
I'm feeling better already.

458
00:27:31,521 --> 00:27:32,563
I told you, didn't I?

459
00:27:33,813 --> 00:27:37,521
Remember I'd told you
to give IIM another shot.

460
00:27:37,813 --> 00:27:41,438
If your bio data had "IIM" on it,

461
00:27:42,230 --> 00:27:44,480
no girl would've turned you down.

462
00:27:49,563 --> 00:27:51,771
Mom, please go,
or you'll miss your flight.

463
00:27:51,855 --> 00:27:52,938
You are yet to pack.

464
00:27:53,021 --> 00:27:54,146
"Go! Go!"

465
00:27:55,271 --> 00:27:57,896
Have you ever said,
"Mom, stay for a couple of days?"

466
00:27:57,980 --> 00:27:59,646
I did ask you to stay.

467
00:28:00,646 --> 00:28:03,230
But he won't leave without you, will he?

468
00:28:03,355 --> 00:28:04,896
You have to babysit him.

469
00:28:04,980 --> 00:28:07,230
Sudha, where's my shaving kit?

470
00:28:07,355 --> 00:28:09,896
Go, give him his "saving" cream.

471
00:28:13,980 --> 00:28:16,521
Why will your shaving cream
be in my purse?

472
00:28:16,855 --> 00:28:21,396
<i>The peacock starts dancing</i>
<i>to attract his mate.</i>

473
00:28:21,771 --> 00:28:22,771
<i>On seeing that,</i>

474
00:28:22,855 --> 00:28:25,188
- <i>the peahen gets attracted.</i>
- What nonsense are you watching?

475
00:28:25,271 --> 00:28:26,230
Come on, get up.

476
00:28:26,355 --> 00:28:28,438
- Sit down and eat. Come on.
- <i>The dance is important.</i>

477
00:28:28,521 --> 00:28:31,646
<i>If she likes the dance,</i>

478
00:28:31,771 --> 00:28:35,646
<i>she picks him as her life partner.</i>

479
00:28:36,230 --> 00:28:39,438
He was quite hot. Why did you refuse him?

480
00:28:39,521 --> 00:28:41,355
Mom, were you checking him out?

481
00:28:41,521 --> 00:28:44,230
Hey, Roshni! Why did you reject him?

482
00:28:45,521 --> 00:28:49,646
Did he do or say something
inappropriate on the terrace?

483
00:28:49,771 --> 00:28:53,105
- Or cracked some non-veg joke?
- Body odor? Bad breath?

484
00:28:53,188 --> 00:28:55,230
Please keep quiet.

485
00:28:55,355 --> 00:28:56,605
Ask her why she rejected him.

486
00:28:56,688 --> 00:28:59,688
Yeah. We really liked him, dear.

487
00:28:59,771 --> 00:29:01,271
His family seemed nice too.

488
00:29:01,355 --> 00:29:02,896
They were genuinely nice.

489
00:29:03,063 --> 00:29:05,230
They wanted to move things along quickly.

490
00:29:05,355 --> 00:29:07,438
No problem. We'll go to their place
tomorrow and clear the air.

491
00:29:07,521 --> 00:29:09,980
Mom, please, I'm not marrying him.

492
00:29:10,105 --> 00:29:12,146
I might marry someone else one day,
but definitely not him.

493
00:29:12,230 --> 00:29:14,021
- You don't want to marry him?
- No.

494
00:29:14,105 --> 00:29:15,730
- You're sure?
- Yes.

495
00:29:15,813 --> 00:29:17,480
- Fine.
- What are you doing?

496
00:29:19,021 --> 00:29:20,438
Then go and meet this one.

497
00:29:21,271 --> 00:29:22,646
Go and meet him tomorrow.

498
00:29:28,646 --> 00:29:31,355
- Come, eat some curry at least.
- I'm not hungry.

499
00:29:33,146 --> 00:29:35,605
This situation has left
a bad taste in my mouth.

500
00:29:35,896 --> 00:29:38,688
I don't think I'll ever be able
to overcome this tragedy.

501
00:29:43,105 --> 00:29:45,105
You are very weird.

502
00:29:45,521 --> 00:29:48,938
Anyway, didn't you go to meet
a prospective bride yesterday?

503
00:29:49,855 --> 00:29:50,730
How did it go?

504
00:29:51,605 --> 00:29:52,730
What do you think?

505
00:29:53,105 --> 00:29:55,688
It went exactly how it goes
with the boss every day.

506
00:29:55,980 --> 00:29:59,105
Feels like I'm destined
to get insulted in every possible way.

507
00:29:59,271 --> 00:30:01,271
After so long, I actually liked a girl.

508
00:30:04,396 --> 00:30:05,563
And she turned me down.

509
00:30:07,521 --> 00:30:08,605
Want a smoke?

510
00:30:09,646 --> 00:30:11,021
Will that fix anything?

511
00:30:11,813 --> 00:30:13,688
No, it'll just ruin your lungs.

512
00:30:13,771 --> 00:30:15,563
And that'll kill you faster.

513
00:30:15,646 --> 00:30:18,188
Your problem will also be solved.
Here you go.

514
00:30:25,938 --> 00:30:27,855
Hey, why don't you come over tonight?

515
00:30:27,938 --> 00:30:30,396
Our colleagues will also be there.
You might feel better.

516
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:32,938
You'll come, yeah? See you.

517
00:30:43,271 --> 00:30:46,146
Thank goodness, the rain finally stopped.

518
00:30:46,980 --> 00:30:48,521
Dad, what if…

519
00:30:51,313 --> 00:30:53,480
I never get married?

520
00:30:58,355 --> 00:31:02,521
Dear, we just got
your mom's blood reports today.

521
00:31:03,355 --> 00:31:04,563
All okay?

522
00:31:06,230 --> 00:31:08,730
Cholesterol, hemoglobin,

523
00:31:09,230 --> 00:31:11,813
thyroid, uric acid…

524
00:31:12,355 --> 00:31:13,521
All normal.

525
00:31:13,605 --> 00:31:14,438
Huh?

526
00:31:14,521 --> 00:31:18,605
So, your mom's sticking around
for at least the next 30 years.

527
00:31:19,438 --> 00:31:21,480
With that in mind, do you really think

528
00:31:21,771 --> 00:31:23,563
she will let you live here alone?

529
00:31:23,646 --> 00:31:24,855
Dad!

530
00:31:31,146 --> 00:31:33,313
- I got you, didn't I?
- Not fair!

531
00:31:49,563 --> 00:31:51,605
Take it easy, everyone.

532
00:31:52,021 --> 00:31:53,938
Calm down. This isn't your home.

533
00:31:54,021 --> 00:31:57,521
Aarav, you don't get to say that.
Don't just hog everything.

534
00:31:57,771 --> 00:32:00,105
Relax, alright?
Come on, guys. Are you ready?

535
00:32:00,980 --> 00:32:02,355
Here, take it.

536
00:32:02,563 --> 00:32:04,646
Come on, take it.

537
00:32:05,355 --> 00:32:06,355
Yeah.

538
00:32:13,355 --> 00:32:14,355
Tell me something.

539
00:32:15,230 --> 00:32:17,396
If you guys were having
a good conversation,

540
00:32:18,105 --> 00:32:19,355
what made her refuse?

541
00:32:19,813 --> 00:32:20,980
Did you ask her?

542
00:32:21,563 --> 00:32:24,105
I did. Called her three times.

543
00:32:24,355 --> 00:32:25,355
She didn't pick up.

544
00:32:25,563 --> 00:32:27,230
You should've called four times.

545
00:32:27,355 --> 00:32:29,521
They usually answer on the fourth try.

546
00:32:29,646 --> 00:32:31,271
You should've asked me first.

547
00:32:31,355 --> 00:32:32,855
Come on, man!

548
00:32:34,355 --> 00:32:36,146
Why would you even say that?

549
00:32:36,396 --> 00:32:38,771
Of course!
Do we have more options for the model?

550
00:32:38,855 --> 00:32:39,730
Yes, Mandy.

551
00:32:39,813 --> 00:32:41,605
Karan, open the other folder.
Open the second…

552
00:32:41,688 --> 00:32:43,896
Well, as far as I am concerned, she was…

553
00:32:43,980 --> 00:32:45,646
yeah, she got a personal invite.

554
00:32:45,771 --> 00:32:47,063
- Second option.
- Really?

555
00:32:47,230 --> 00:32:48,438
Look at her forehead!

556
00:32:48,521 --> 00:32:50,146
We're not here to play
lawn tennis on it, Rosh!

557
00:32:50,230 --> 00:32:51,771
Yeah, I have another option.

558
00:32:51,855 --> 00:32:53,646
I'm just sorry. My life…

559
00:32:53,771 --> 00:32:55,646
- Yeah, more options, please.
- Yeah.

560
00:32:55,813 --> 00:32:57,521
This is the second one.

561
00:32:57,646 --> 00:32:58,646
Move ahead.

562
00:32:58,813 --> 00:33:01,021
Yeah. Well, this one
you selected last time.

563
00:33:01,105 --> 00:33:02,980
I did not. Move ahead.

564
00:33:03,105 --> 00:33:04,063
Option three.

565
00:33:04,146 --> 00:33:05,230
No.

566
00:33:05,355 --> 00:33:07,438
- You really liked her.
- I did not. I don't remember.

567
00:33:07,521 --> 00:33:08,646
Okay, next.

568
00:33:09,355 --> 00:33:11,230
This just does not work!

569
00:33:11,438 --> 00:33:14,188
Look, I'm sorry.
I won't be able to leave at this rate.

570
00:33:14,271 --> 00:33:15,771
Yeah, let me just finish this.

571
00:33:16,230 --> 00:33:20,313
Okay, redo the entire shoot
and get in touch with Aura Talent.

572
00:33:20,688 --> 00:33:23,021
Rosh, beauty sells.

573
00:33:23,188 --> 00:33:25,730
Bring me pretty faces.
What is all this nonsense?

574
00:33:29,521 --> 00:33:32,355
"Bring me pretty faces.
What is all this nonsense?"

575
00:33:34,521 --> 00:33:36,105
Oh, my God!

576
00:33:37,646 --> 00:33:41,146
- I'm going to go. Are you coming?
- No, go ahead. I'll take this call.

577
00:33:41,230 --> 00:33:43,563
- Okay, see you.
- See you.

578
00:33:46,271 --> 00:33:47,355
<i>Hello?</i>

579
00:33:47,980 --> 00:33:50,355
<i>I missed a few calls from this number.</i>

580
00:33:51,021 --> 00:33:52,146
"Rosni?"

581
00:33:52,271 --> 00:33:53,230
Roshni.

582
00:33:53,355 --> 00:33:56,813
<i>Correct! It's me, "Sasank."</i>

583
00:33:56,980 --> 00:34:00,813
Remember, we were on the terrace
the other day and took the clothes off?

584
00:34:01,438 --> 00:34:03,396
Took the clothes off?

585
00:34:03,646 --> 00:34:04,730
I just wanted

586
00:34:04,813 --> 00:34:06,896
<i>to know why you said 'no' to me.</i>

587
00:34:06,980 --> 00:34:09,105
Yeah, ask her…

588
00:34:09,646 --> 00:34:13,521
I know you smiled that day.
So, I thought…

589
00:34:13,688 --> 00:34:15,230
Talk to her.

590
00:34:17,105 --> 00:34:18,105
She hung up.

591
00:34:18,355 --> 00:34:19,230
She hung up?

592
00:34:20,563 --> 00:34:22,563
Who told you to rush like that?

593
00:34:22,855 --> 00:34:24,438
You need to take it slow.

594
00:34:24,646 --> 00:34:26,688
You took your clothes off
on the first meeting?

595
00:34:26,771 --> 00:34:29,105
It's okay, you'll get
the hang of it eventually.

596
00:34:30,105 --> 00:34:31,313
All the best.

597
00:34:32,188 --> 00:34:33,771
Let's go already.

598
00:34:33,855 --> 00:34:35,438
- Come on, let's go.
- Come on.

599
00:34:43,980 --> 00:34:45,188
Shashank…

600
00:34:45,271 --> 00:34:47,855
Shashank!

601
00:34:48,355 --> 00:34:49,521
Hey, Shashank!

602
00:34:50,396 --> 00:34:52,771
It was a well-planned strategy.

603
00:34:52,980 --> 00:34:54,646
It was so nicely detailed.

604
00:34:55,521 --> 00:34:57,980
Mr. Arora asked you a few questions

605
00:34:58,105 --> 00:35:01,230
you already knew the answers to,
but you stayed quiet.

606
00:35:01,813 --> 00:35:02,730
Why?

607
00:35:09,105 --> 00:35:10,646
If I hadn't been here today,

608
00:35:10,813 --> 00:35:12,438
we would've lost the deal.

609
00:35:13,938 --> 00:35:16,355
How long am I going
to keep saving you, Shashank?

610
00:35:20,313 --> 00:35:22,730
You're in marketing. Speak up!

611
00:35:23,021 --> 00:35:26,063
How are you supposed to sell anything
if you don't say a word?

612
00:35:45,438 --> 00:35:46,355
Sir…

613
00:35:48,355 --> 00:35:49,563
Can I get you something?

614
00:35:51,271 --> 00:35:52,480
Ice tea?

615
00:35:52,938 --> 00:35:53,938
Cold coffee?

616
00:36:00,646 --> 00:36:02,396
Sir, no matter what the problem is,

617
00:36:02,563 --> 00:36:04,271
no matter how tough things get,

618
00:36:04,771 --> 00:36:06,355
it's going to be okay.

619
00:36:06,688 --> 00:36:08,480
Just have patience, sir.

620
00:36:11,771 --> 00:36:13,021
Sir…

621
00:36:16,146 --> 00:36:17,938
My name literally means patience.

622
00:36:18,271 --> 00:36:19,605
That's all you need.

623
00:36:43,563 --> 00:36:44,855
"Rosni!"

624
00:37:09,146 --> 00:37:10,313
"Rosni!"

625
00:37:11,813 --> 00:37:13,563
Listen…

626
00:37:16,855 --> 00:37:19,521
It's okay. She'll be back tomorrow.

627
00:37:19,771 --> 00:37:21,146
Don't worry.

628
00:37:27,855 --> 00:37:32,146
Hey, she's going to take
another five minutes to leave.

629
00:37:32,813 --> 00:37:34,563
Go, sit by the fountain. Okay?

630
00:37:34,688 --> 00:37:36,938
You're blocking the way for others.

631
00:37:38,563 --> 00:37:40,980
Just sit down.
I'll tell you when she heads out.

632
00:37:48,521 --> 00:37:49,855
Want some tea?

633
00:38:08,271 --> 00:38:09,980
Hey! Excuse me!

634
00:38:10,105 --> 00:38:11,938
At least tell me why you said 'no'.

635
00:38:12,355 --> 00:38:14,146
Isn't a simple 'no' enough?

636
00:38:18,271 --> 00:38:20,271
<i>Don't worry, dear.</i>

637
00:38:20,355 --> 00:38:22,646
<i>It's her loss.</i>

638
00:38:23,521 --> 00:38:26,355
- <i>There's nothing lacking in you.</i>
- Right, Mom.

639
00:38:26,646 --> 00:38:31,563
Son, do you think she rejected you
for the same reason I'm thinking?

640
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:33,771
It has to be that.

641
00:38:33,938 --> 00:38:35,063
What else could it be?

642
00:38:37,771 --> 00:38:41,271
If we'd known,
we wouldn't have named you this.

643
00:38:41,855 --> 00:38:44,105
There were so many other options, right?

644
00:38:44,230 --> 00:38:48,355
Like Pankaj, Ajay, Mohan…

645
00:38:48,646 --> 00:38:50,105
<i>Rakesh.</i>

646
00:38:50,230 --> 00:38:52,355
Not "Rakes", Mom.

647
00:38:52,813 --> 00:38:54,563
Is that for Karan? I'll take it.

648
00:39:03,355 --> 00:39:05,938
Madam, are you looking for the guy
in the blue shirt?

649
00:39:08,438 --> 00:39:09,771
Hey, blue shirt!

650
00:39:10,271 --> 00:39:11,771
Hey! Blue shirt!

651
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:18,480
Mind your own business.

652
00:39:21,313 --> 00:39:22,730
Mind your own business!

653
00:40:09,355 --> 00:40:10,355
See!

654
00:40:11,021 --> 00:40:11,896
Mom!

655
00:40:11,980 --> 00:40:13,105
Even he found someone!

656
00:40:14,438 --> 00:40:15,563
She is pretty.

657
00:40:18,938 --> 00:40:20,063
It's okay.

658
00:40:20,521 --> 00:40:22,521
Your mom still has plenty of options.

659
00:40:26,355 --> 00:40:28,355
You should stay hydrated, dear.

660
00:40:30,771 --> 00:40:32,980
I've kept some water here. Bye-bye.

661
00:40:52,188 --> 00:40:53,313
Hello?

662
00:40:54,355 --> 00:40:55,896
Why didn't you come over today?

663
00:40:57,188 --> 00:40:58,688
<i>You told me not to.</i>

664
00:40:59,730 --> 00:41:00,730
Hmm.

665
00:41:03,396 --> 00:41:05,896
If you're free tomorrow…

666
00:41:06,230 --> 00:41:07,521
want to meet for coffee?

667
00:41:08,563 --> 00:41:10,563
I'd come even if I were busy.

668
00:41:40,688 --> 00:41:41,980
"Rosni."

669
00:41:51,355 --> 00:41:53,230
Sorry, I took a wrong turn.

670
00:41:53,355 --> 00:41:55,355
I would've been here sooner otherwise.

671
00:41:56,230 --> 00:41:57,146
It's okay.

672
00:41:57,230 --> 00:41:59,646
You made it,
and that's more than enough for me.

673
00:42:00,605 --> 00:42:02,646
So, how's your day been?

674
00:42:03,771 --> 00:42:06,980
Half done. I'm about to find out the rest.

675
00:42:10,230 --> 00:42:11,355
Well…

676
00:42:13,021 --> 00:42:14,021
Water?

677
00:42:15,813 --> 00:42:19,271
By the way, I think
I know why you rejected me.

678
00:42:20,646 --> 00:42:22,063
You know?

679
00:42:22,521 --> 00:42:24,230
- Yeah.
- Tell me.

680
00:42:25,146 --> 00:42:28,355
- I have trouble pronouncing 'sh'.
- What?

681
00:42:28,438 --> 00:42:30,480
Yeah, I mispronounce words
with 'sh' in them.

682
00:42:30,563 --> 00:42:31,730
Shah Rukh Khan becomes "Sah" Rukh Khan.

683
00:42:31,813 --> 00:42:33,938
My parents named me "Sasank Sarma",

684
00:42:34,021 --> 00:42:35,771
and you're "Rosni" to me.

685
00:42:36,230 --> 00:42:39,688
My boss' name is "Sekhar",
and my colleague is "Manis".

686
00:42:40,813 --> 00:42:42,605
And this is the tragedy of my life.

687
00:42:42,688 --> 00:42:45,563
- Well, it's okay.
- Wait a second…

688
00:42:45,646 --> 00:42:49,271
You think I rejected you
because you can't pronounce 'sh' properly?

689
00:42:49,355 --> 00:42:51,855
Maybe.

690
00:42:52,855 --> 00:42:56,188
No. Listen, Shashank,
I think you are perfect.

691
00:42:56,271 --> 00:42:57,355
In fact, you know,

692
00:42:57,521 --> 00:43:00,438
my mom actually declared you hot.

693
00:43:05,355 --> 00:43:07,105
Can I ask you something personal?

694
00:43:07,313 --> 00:43:08,605
Hmm.

695
00:43:09,355 --> 00:43:11,730
You've been living in Mumbai for so long,

696
00:43:12,146 --> 00:43:14,146
so you must've had a girlfriend, right?

697
00:43:14,438 --> 00:43:17,021
Why? Is that a rule in the city?

698
00:43:17,230 --> 00:43:19,563
No! It's just that

699
00:43:19,771 --> 00:43:22,438
you're good-looking, a little funny, and--

700
00:43:22,521 --> 00:43:23,896
And yet, you rejected me.

701
00:43:29,605 --> 00:43:30,730
Who's Nikita?

702
00:43:32,105 --> 00:43:32,980
Nikita?

703
00:43:34,021 --> 00:43:35,146
Yeah, Nikita.

704
00:43:36,730 --> 00:43:38,396
You know what? Just forget it.

705
00:43:38,563 --> 00:43:39,813
Nikki!

706
00:43:40,313 --> 00:43:42,855
Nikki? She's my cousin.

707
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:45,563
Cousin?

708
00:43:45,646 --> 00:43:46,771
Yeah.

709
00:43:46,980 --> 00:43:48,480
Right, your cousin.

710
00:43:48,646 --> 00:43:49,646
Right.

711
00:43:51,105 --> 00:43:52,980
Why? Who did you think she was?

712
00:43:53,230 --> 00:43:54,730
No, it's nothing.

713
00:43:57,480 --> 00:44:01,480
So… your boyfriend?

714
00:44:05,063 --> 00:44:07,188
I had someone. It didn't work out.

715
00:44:10,563 --> 00:44:12,480
May I ask why? If you don't mind?

716
00:44:12,646 --> 00:44:15,438
All the personal questions
in the first meeting?

717
00:44:16,105 --> 00:44:18,313
So, is there a chance of a second one?

718
00:44:20,771 --> 00:44:21,855
It's just that…

719
00:44:24,355 --> 00:44:25,563
I…

720
00:44:27,730 --> 00:44:30,313
I just wanted to tell you
that I can't marry you.

721
00:44:30,771 --> 00:44:31,646
Why not?

722
00:44:33,480 --> 00:44:34,730
I'm sorry.

723
00:44:51,105 --> 00:44:54,063
<i>So, what kind of girl are you looking for?</i>

724
00:44:56,855 --> 00:44:59,563
<i>I mean, do you have a list?</i>

725
00:45:00,896 --> 00:45:03,480
<i>A list? I'm not out grocery shopping.</i>

726
00:45:04,355 --> 00:45:07,605
<i>I just want someone who feels like home.</i>

727
00:45:09,771 --> 00:45:13,021
<i>I mean, someone like you.</i>

728
00:45:14,396 --> 00:45:16,730
<i>By the way,</i>
<i>are those prescription glasses?</i>

729
00:45:16,855 --> 00:45:19,230
<i>Does anyone wear glasses</i>
<i>without a prescription?</i>

730
00:45:19,313 --> 00:45:21,730
<i>Would you be okay</i>
<i>with someone who wears glasses?</i>

731
00:45:22,521 --> 00:45:26,938
<i>I'm okay. I don't mind it.</i>

732
00:45:31,730 --> 00:45:33,521
<i>- "Rosni!'</i>
<i>- Yeah?</i>

733
00:45:33,605 --> 00:45:36,438
<i>Listen, I…</i>

734
00:45:38,313 --> 00:45:39,438
<i>Forget it.</i>

735
00:45:42,980 --> 00:45:45,230
<i>So what do you do</i>
<i>when you're in a bad mood?</i>

736
00:45:45,730 --> 00:45:47,230
<i>I eat.</i>

737
00:45:47,813 --> 00:45:48,938
<i>You?</i>

738
00:45:49,938 --> 00:45:51,313
<i>I cook.</i>

739
00:46:30,480 --> 00:46:31,480
Hey!

740
00:46:35,771 --> 00:46:37,938
J-Just a second!

741
00:46:51,730 --> 00:46:52,896
Hi!

742
00:46:59,938 --> 00:47:03,146
H-How did you even get my address?

743
00:47:03,438 --> 00:47:04,855
It was in your bio-data,

744
00:47:04,980 --> 00:47:08,146
right under the part where
it says your uncle's an IIT graduate.

745
00:47:18,355 --> 00:47:19,771
It's beautiful.

746
00:47:30,646 --> 00:47:32,730
- Coffee?
- Sure.

747
00:47:53,646 --> 00:47:57,938
I click a few pictures
when I see someone interesting.

748
00:47:59,146 --> 00:47:59,980
Oh!

749
00:48:00,605 --> 00:48:02,438
I thought they were your relatives.

750
00:48:09,563 --> 00:48:10,605
Come, have a seat.

751
00:48:23,438 --> 00:48:24,980
Why are you doing this?

752
00:48:28,480 --> 00:48:30,771
What did you find so interesting in me?

753
00:48:32,855 --> 00:48:34,271
The very thing I don't have.

754
00:48:36,355 --> 00:48:37,480
Boobs?

755
00:48:37,980 --> 00:48:39,730
What? No!

756
00:48:41,313 --> 00:48:43,063
Your confidence.

757
00:48:43,896 --> 00:48:45,771
I wish I had that.

758
00:48:49,855 --> 00:48:51,230
I really like you.

759
00:48:58,646 --> 00:49:00,105
I really…

760
00:49:02,438 --> 00:49:04,355
like your coffee.

761
00:49:04,771 --> 00:49:06,188
Coffee.

762
00:49:08,730 --> 00:49:10,146
Oops!

763
00:49:12,896 --> 00:49:14,188
Chips.

764
00:49:19,980 --> 00:49:21,438
Thank you.

765
00:49:28,646 --> 00:49:30,688
Do you know why I rejected you?

766
00:49:31,438 --> 00:49:33,063
Because I think you're…

767
00:49:33,771 --> 00:49:36,105
you're Baskin-Robbins.

768
00:49:36,188 --> 00:49:38,813
And I'm just an orange candy.

769
00:49:40,355 --> 00:49:41,771
Orange candy?

770
00:49:44,355 --> 00:49:45,646
Look at that!

771
00:49:47,355 --> 00:49:49,355
I've loved orange candy

772
00:49:49,480 --> 00:49:50,771
since I was a kid.

773
00:49:53,313 --> 00:49:54,855
You're crazy.

774
00:49:55,771 --> 00:49:56,938
That I am.

775
00:50:01,730 --> 00:50:04,480
- Don't you have to leave for work?
- Yeah, I do.

776
00:50:05,480 --> 00:50:06,896
Bye.

777
00:50:16,896 --> 00:50:18,813
Your glasses are getting in the way.

778
00:50:19,480 --> 00:50:22,521
You're getting in the way,
the glasses have always been there.

779
00:50:24,563 --> 00:50:26,605
So, are these for seeing far or near?

780
00:50:29,146 --> 00:50:31,146
Things really close to me.

781
00:50:35,646 --> 00:50:36,980
- Okay, listen.
- Yes?

782
00:50:37,105 --> 00:50:40,271
Whether you say 'sh' as 'sa' or 'fa',

783
00:50:40,355 --> 00:50:41,730
it doesn't matter to me.

784
00:50:43,480 --> 00:50:44,563
Are you "fure"?

785
00:50:46,563 --> 00:50:48,105
Hundred percent "fure".

786
00:50:49,563 --> 00:50:50,563
Bye!

787
00:50:50,813 --> 00:50:52,063
Bye.

788
