<i>The questions like why</i>

822
00:53:00,313 --> 00:53:02,605
<i>And where can wait</i>

823
00:53:17,771 --> 00:53:20,480
"Rosni", should we tell
our parents about us?

824
00:53:20,646 --> 00:53:23,105
Naina already knows, that's enough.

825
00:53:24,146 --> 00:53:25,896
What's the rush?

826
00:53:26,105 --> 00:53:27,355
Let's be sure first.

827
00:53:30,563 --> 00:53:34,605
"Rosni",
I've never been more sure in my life.

828
00:53:34,813 --> 00:53:36,146
So what's the problem?

829
00:53:38,105 --> 00:53:39,646
That's what Sahil said too.

830
00:53:43,563 --> 00:53:44,813
Sahil?

831
00:53:49,480 --> 00:53:51,480
Yeah, we dated for two years.

832
00:53:52,063 --> 00:53:54,480
The wedding invites
were already out. And…

833
00:53:55,855 --> 00:53:58,313
A week before the wedding, he just said…

834
00:54:00,230 --> 00:54:01,688
He wasn't sure.

835
00:54:01,771 --> 00:54:02,980
Huh?

836
00:54:06,855 --> 00:54:08,813
He never gave me a reason, but…

837
00:54:11,730 --> 00:54:16,105
Shashank, the girl he married
is very different from me.

838
00:54:29,646 --> 00:54:31,271
Can I get Sahil's address?

839
00:54:32,146 --> 00:54:33,230
Why?

840
00:54:33,646 --> 00:54:36,105
I want to send him flowers
and a 'thank you' note.

841
00:54:36,355 --> 00:54:38,271
We're together because of him.

842
00:54:38,355 --> 00:54:40,271
If he had stayed,
I wouldn't be here with you.

843
00:54:40,355 --> 00:54:41,688
Shashank.

844
00:54:42,230 --> 00:54:43,105
Hi!

845
00:54:43,980 --> 00:54:45,646
- Order?
- Yes.

846
00:54:46,938 --> 00:54:48,563
Have you tried this here?

847
00:54:49,105 --> 00:54:50,063
What? From where?

848
00:54:50,146 --> 00:54:51,688
This thing from this place.

849
00:54:51,771 --> 00:54:54,313
The second one from the top,
third from the bottom.

850
00:54:54,646 --> 00:54:57,646
Oh! Does this dish have a name?

851
00:54:57,730 --> 00:54:59,980
Yeah, it does. You can read it.

852
00:55:01,355 --> 00:55:03,146
They've got great pasta too.

853
00:55:03,230 --> 00:55:04,230
- Right?
- Yeah.

854
00:55:04,355 --> 00:55:05,188
Pasta.

855
00:55:05,271 --> 00:55:07,896
No, I want the dish you suggested earlier.

856
00:55:07,980 --> 00:55:09,646
Shashank, place the order.

857
00:55:12,855 --> 00:55:16,021
Two <i>Shawarmas</i>
and two chocolate shakes, coming up.

858
00:55:17,105 --> 00:55:18,146
Hmm?

859
00:55:21,605 --> 00:55:22,855
Why didn't you order?

860
00:55:23,021 --> 00:55:24,355
He got it.

861
00:55:26,480 --> 00:55:28,105
- Tuning.
- Yeah, some tuning!

862
00:55:31,730 --> 00:55:34,313
- Listen, "Rosni".
- Yes.

863
00:55:35,230 --> 00:55:38,563
I've been meaning
to tell you something for a while.

864
00:55:38,980 --> 00:55:40,230
Say it.

865
00:55:40,855 --> 00:55:42,230
Well…

866
00:55:44,271 --> 00:55:47,188
Forget it. I don't want to kill the vibe.

867
00:55:48,980 --> 00:55:50,980
- I've been asking forever, just tell me.
- I…

868
00:55:51,063 --> 00:55:53,230
- Something wrong at work?
- No.

869
00:55:54,646 --> 00:55:56,521
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, sure.

870
00:55:56,730 --> 00:56:00,021
- My train's here, Shashank. Just tell me!
- Go on.

871
00:56:00,230 --> 00:56:02,271
- Any family issues?
- No.

872
00:56:02,355 --> 00:56:04,938
- Did you fight with Anil?
- Let's talk tomorrow. Go.

873
00:56:10,355 --> 00:56:12,396
- Please, just tell me.
- I will.

874
00:56:12,480 --> 00:56:14,230
I'll see you tomorrow. Bye.

875
00:56:43,980 --> 00:56:45,438
- It's fresh, right?
- Yeah.

876
00:56:46,396 --> 00:56:48,355
- Hot coffee?
- Yes, please.

877
00:56:57,605 --> 00:57:01,313
So what did you want to tell me?
You've had me in suspense since yesterday.

878
00:57:03,855 --> 00:57:06,646
Hey! What are you doing?

879
00:57:06,771 --> 00:57:09,396
- Come on, spill it.
- Why are you getting so violent?

880
00:57:09,605 --> 00:57:11,771
I skipped my yoga class for this,
you know.

881
00:57:13,105 --> 00:57:14,105
I'll tell you.

882
00:57:20,480 --> 00:57:22,105
Shashank, please just tell me.

883
00:57:22,521 --> 00:57:23,688
Well…

884
00:57:25,730 --> 00:57:29,188
Remember my dad saying
I almost made it into IIM?

885
00:57:29,271 --> 00:57:33,313
- Yeah.
- That's not true.

886
00:57:35,396 --> 00:57:37,896
Well, I really had been selected.

887
00:57:37,980 --> 00:57:40,271
But I didn't go for the interview.

888
00:57:40,896 --> 00:57:44,480
The moment I heard of the interview
and a group discussion,

889
00:57:44,563 --> 00:57:46,355
I couldn't bring myself to go in.

890
00:57:47,146 --> 00:57:50,105
So I told everyone I'd been rejected.

891
00:57:50,230 --> 00:57:51,480
That's it.

892
00:57:52,730 --> 00:57:53,896
It's okay.

893
00:57:57,646 --> 00:57:58,730
I feel so light now.

894
00:57:58,855 --> 00:58:00,771
- Hmm?
- Yeah, I feel nice.

895
00:58:03,688 --> 00:58:05,938
You know what?
I've never told this to anyone.

896
00:58:07,105 --> 00:58:08,271
Not even my mom.

897
00:58:08,355 --> 00:58:09,480
You're the first one.

898
00:58:11,105 --> 00:58:12,021
Really?

899
00:58:12,146 --> 00:58:13,105
Yeah.

900
00:58:18,313 --> 00:58:20,438
Shashank, you know…

901
00:58:23,355 --> 00:58:25,855
This thing between us…

902
00:58:25,980 --> 00:58:27,480
What? Love?

903
00:58:30,105 --> 00:58:31,146
Trust?

904
00:58:31,730 --> 00:58:32,896
"Emoson?"

905
00:58:32,980 --> 00:58:34,063
No.

906
00:58:34,855 --> 00:58:36,063
"Connecson?"

907
00:58:36,146 --> 00:58:37,146
No.

908
00:58:38,980 --> 00:58:40,105
Intimacy?

909
00:58:40,605 --> 00:58:41,771
Glasses.

910
00:58:43,646 --> 00:58:44,730
Glasses?

911
00:58:47,980 --> 00:58:50,230
These aren't prescription glasses.

912
00:58:52,980 --> 00:58:54,230
Then why wear them?

913
00:58:55,355 --> 00:58:57,355
Because I think…

914
00:58:58,230 --> 00:59:00,813
My nose looks weird without them.

915
00:59:00,896 --> 00:59:02,146
What?

916
00:59:04,063 --> 00:59:06,605
Your nose is my favorite thing
about your face.

917
00:59:07,646 --> 00:59:09,396
It's so cute.

918
00:59:09,855 --> 00:59:13,105
When you do this, it's like magic.

919
00:59:14,230 --> 00:59:15,480
Do it for me just once.

920
00:59:15,563 --> 00:59:16,855
Please do it.

921
00:59:16,980 --> 00:59:18,771
- No, Shashank.
- Please.

922
00:59:19,396 --> 00:59:20,605
Do it.

923
00:59:20,771 --> 00:59:22,021
Yes, that!

924
00:59:22,563 --> 00:59:23,896
Now take the glasses off.

925
00:59:23,980 --> 00:59:25,188
- No, I won't.
- Take them off.

926
00:59:25,271 --> 00:59:26,896
No Shashank, not my glasses.

927
00:59:26,980 --> 00:59:30,480
Not my glasses, Shashank. No…

928
00:59:46,230 --> 00:59:47,355
Congratulations!

929
00:59:47,438 --> 00:59:50,021
- We just bought a brand-new car!
- What!

930
00:59:54,980 --> 00:59:57,313
Oh, my God!

931
00:59:57,396 --> 00:59:58,480
When did this happen?

932
00:59:58,646 --> 00:59:59,480
Well…

933
01:00:02,980 --> 01:00:05,105
I'm so proud of you.

934
01:00:15,813 --> 01:00:16,646
Dad…

935
01:00:18,563 --> 01:00:19,396
<i>Hello?</i>

936
01:00:19,563 --> 01:00:22,605
<i>I heard you bought a car.</i>

937
01:00:23,313 --> 01:00:24,688
<i>Now go, buy a house too.</i>

938
01:00:25,188 --> 01:00:27,855
<i>Don't take another four years</i>
<i>to buy one, okay?</i>

939
01:00:28,396 --> 01:00:29,688
<i>I'm hanging up.</i>

940
01:00:29,855 --> 01:00:30,771
Okay, Dad.

941
01:00:33,021 --> 01:00:34,396
I can't remember

942
01:00:34,980 --> 01:00:37,105
the last time he was proud of me.

943
01:00:39,855 --> 01:00:43,730
It was when you almost cracked
the IIM interview.

944
01:00:47,396 --> 01:00:49,396
- Listen, "Rosni".
- Yes?

945
01:00:52,855 --> 01:00:54,771
Take your glasses off, please.

946
01:00:57,480 --> 01:01:00,480
Of all the things,
you could ask me to take off,

947
01:01:00,646 --> 01:01:01,855
my glasses.

948
01:01:04,730 --> 01:01:05,730
Come on.

949
01:01:07,396 --> 01:01:09,188
You're so cute.

950
01:01:19,105 --> 01:01:20,355
What the…

951
01:01:20,646 --> 01:01:21,563
Hey!

952
01:01:21,730 --> 01:01:23,105
What happened, bro?

953
01:01:23,563 --> 01:01:24,396
Nothing…

954
01:01:25,396 --> 01:01:26,646
I…

955
01:01:26,730 --> 01:01:28,021
You scratched it!

956
01:01:28,105 --> 01:01:30,563
Where? On your car or your heart?

957
01:01:31,438 --> 01:01:32,896
You… wait right there.

958
01:01:32,980 --> 01:01:34,313
Hold on, my dear.

959
01:01:34,396 --> 01:01:36,563
I'm going to wreak havoc today.

960
01:01:37,146 --> 01:01:38,730
Hey, wait!

961
01:01:45,230 --> 01:01:46,480
Don't be scared.

962
01:01:53,271 --> 01:01:55,563
Chill, bro.
It's a small scratch, no big deal.

963
01:01:55,646 --> 01:01:57,313
I'll get my car tomorrow,
you can scratch it again.

964
01:01:57,396 --> 01:01:59,563
My girlfriend's with me today,
and it's a matter of love

965
01:01:59,646 --> 01:02:01,146
so please cut me some slack.

966
01:02:01,230 --> 01:02:02,396
I won't go overboard.

967
01:02:02,563 --> 01:02:06,146
I'll just grab your collar, your hair
and give a couple of punches each.

968
01:02:06,230 --> 01:02:07,646
- Okay?
- No way!

969
01:02:07,980 --> 01:02:09,313
That's extreme.

970
01:02:09,396 --> 01:02:11,480
One each would be too little.

971
01:02:11,771 --> 01:02:13,688
How about two each? It sounds fair.

972
01:02:13,771 --> 01:02:14,688
You can charge me.

973
01:02:14,771 --> 01:02:17,146
I'll pay you online, okay?

974
01:02:17,271 --> 01:02:18,730
- Will you?
- Yeah, I will.

975
01:02:18,855 --> 01:02:19,980
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

976
01:02:20,230 --> 01:02:21,646
- Fine.
- Fine?

977
01:02:24,646 --> 01:02:25,730
Ready?

978
01:02:27,271 --> 01:02:28,271
Take it easy.

979
01:02:34,271 --> 01:02:35,771
Not my hair.

980
01:02:35,855 --> 01:02:37,896
Not the hair? Where do I hit then?

981
01:02:38,105 --> 01:02:39,480
My stomach.

982
01:02:45,855 --> 01:02:47,730
Look behind you… the bald guy!

983
01:02:47,813 --> 01:02:49,188
Grab him!

984
01:02:49,355 --> 01:02:50,646
Punch him hard!

985
01:02:51,396 --> 01:02:54,063
- Come on, Shashank! Come on!
- My God!

986
01:02:54,480 --> 01:02:56,021
Blood!

987
01:02:56,355 --> 01:02:57,480
You…

988
01:02:57,646 --> 01:02:58,855
Shashank!

989
01:03:01,896 --> 01:03:03,980
Feeling proud of yourself today?

990
01:03:04,563 --> 01:03:07,021
You weren't happy
with just a scratch on the car.

991
01:03:07,105 --> 01:03:08,771
Now how am I supposed
to do it with one hand?

992
01:03:08,855 --> 01:03:09,771
What?

993
01:03:10,480 --> 01:03:12,355
- Work.
- Oh!

994
01:03:12,480 --> 01:03:13,355
Work.

995
01:03:13,480 --> 01:03:15,646
I'll put an ice pack on it. Hold on.

996
01:03:19,396 --> 01:03:20,688
What are you doing?

997
01:03:20,771 --> 01:03:22,105
What if someone hears you?

998
01:03:26,188 --> 01:03:28,021
DAD

999
01:03:31,396 --> 01:03:33,896
Mr. Fragile.

1000
01:03:37,771 --> 01:03:40,230
Listen, it's pretty late.

1001
01:03:42,230 --> 01:03:43,480
Hmm.

1002
01:03:44,355 --> 01:03:45,646
Go home.

1003
01:03:46,855 --> 01:03:49,355
You expect me to leave you like this?

1004
01:03:49,480 --> 01:03:50,646
No.

1005
01:03:50,896 --> 01:03:52,396
But you will have to.

1006
01:03:58,980 --> 01:04:00,230
Hey!

1007
01:04:01,646 --> 01:04:04,480
- Bye, see you tomorrow.
- Bye.

1008
01:04:08,896 --> 01:04:10,396
- Hello?
- <i>Hello?</i>

1009
01:04:10,480 --> 01:04:11,896
Hello, Dad. I seek your blessings.

1010
01:04:11,980 --> 01:04:14,480
- Hello?
- <i>Hello? Hello?</i>

1011
01:04:14,646 --> 01:04:16,605
I can't hear you.

1012
01:04:17,146 --> 01:04:19,980
<i>Is that true or are you pretending</i>
<i>that you can't hear me?</i>

1013
01:04:22,896 --> 01:04:26,480
Hello? Dad, can we talk tomorrow?

1014
01:04:26,563 --> 01:04:29,771
I've got tons of work. I don't have time.

1015
01:04:29,980 --> 01:04:32,105
<i>Then make time.</i>

1016
01:04:32,230 --> 01:04:34,230
<i>If I hadn't made time back then,</i>

1017
01:04:34,355 --> 01:04:36,646
<i>you wouldn't even exist, got it?</i>

1018
01:04:36,855 --> 01:04:39,855
<i>We've got a marriage proposal</i>
<i>for you. Go, meet her tomorrow.</i>

1019
01:04:39,938 --> 01:04:41,063
<i>I'll send her details.</i>

1020
01:04:41,230 --> 01:04:42,480
Dad, about the girl…

1021
01:04:42,563 --> 01:04:43,980
Hello? Hello, Dad?

1022
01:04:53,688 --> 01:04:54,938
Hi, sir.

1023
01:04:57,813 --> 01:04:59,146
What can I get you, sir?

1024
01:04:59,855 --> 01:05:02,521
Do you want something
from the top or the bottom, sir?

1025
01:05:03,855 --> 01:05:05,646
A normal coffee,
the kind that normal people drink.

1026
01:05:05,730 --> 01:05:06,896
Right, sir.

1027
01:05:06,980 --> 01:05:08,021
And for you, ma'am?

1028
01:05:10,146 --> 01:05:12,521
An avocado toast
and a black coffee, please.

1029
01:05:12,605 --> 01:05:16,396
By the way, what caught your eye
on my matrimonial profile?

1030
01:05:16,688 --> 01:05:17,855
Actually…

1031
01:05:18,480 --> 01:05:22,230
my dad asked me to come and meet you.

1032
01:05:22,855 --> 01:05:24,146
I like how real you are.

1033
01:05:24,271 --> 01:05:25,980
Raw and desi.

1034
01:05:26,105 --> 01:05:28,563
You sound like you're describing
a chicken, not a person.

1035
01:05:28,646 --> 01:05:30,438
Raw and desi.

1036
01:05:30,521 --> 01:05:32,063
You're so funny!

1037
01:05:32,146 --> 01:05:35,063
Listen… I have a girlfriend.

1038
01:05:35,271 --> 01:05:36,521
Tell me something new…

1039
01:05:36,605 --> 01:05:37,813
Oops, sorry!

1040
01:05:40,730 --> 01:05:42,980
No, seriously. I have a girlfriend.

1041
01:05:43,230 --> 01:05:44,355
What?

1042
01:05:47,855 --> 01:05:49,355
"Rosni!"

1043
01:05:49,646 --> 01:05:50,730
"Shit!"

1044
01:05:51,646 --> 01:05:52,855
I… I'm sorry.

1045
01:05:52,980 --> 01:05:54,105
Sorry.

1046
01:05:54,355 --> 01:05:56,146
Sorry. It's okay.

1047
01:05:58,230 --> 01:05:59,480
"Rosni!"

1048
01:06:01,230 --> 01:06:03,688
"Rosni…"

1049
01:06:06,980 --> 01:06:09,230
"Rosni!"

1050
01:06:09,313 --> 01:06:11,563
- Hear me out.
- You're exactly like Sahil!

1051
01:06:11,646 --> 01:06:12,730
What?

1052
01:06:12,980 --> 01:06:16,105
This is exactly
why I wanted you to be sure.

1053
01:06:16,230 --> 01:06:18,313
What are you saying?
Let's sit somewhere--

1054
01:06:18,396 --> 01:06:19,980
What do you want to talk about?

1055
01:06:20,105 --> 01:06:22,271
Did you think
you can keep exploring options

1056
01:06:22,355 --> 01:06:23,896
and maybe find someone better?

1057
01:06:23,980 --> 01:06:26,063
What do you mean?
I'm not shopping for a "wasing" machine

1058
01:06:26,146 --> 01:06:27,146
that I'll find a better option.

1059
01:06:27,230 --> 01:06:30,355
My dad's been pressuring me
to meet her, so I did.

1060
01:06:30,438 --> 01:06:32,021
I was going to say 'no' anyway.

1061
01:06:32,105 --> 01:06:35,355
You didn't sound like someone
who was going to say 'no'.

1062
01:06:35,771 --> 01:06:37,021
You know what, Shashank?

1063
01:06:37,271 --> 01:06:39,063
You should be with someone like her.

1064
01:06:39,146 --> 01:06:40,480
I don't fit with you.

1065
01:06:40,646 --> 01:06:41,813
She's perfect for you.

1066
01:06:41,896 --> 01:06:44,021
What? To hell with being perfect!

1067
01:06:44,105 --> 01:06:45,813
I… I like you.

1068
01:06:45,896 --> 01:06:48,896
I like your laugh,
your temper, your madness.

1069
01:06:48,980 --> 01:06:50,480
You're my perfect match.

1070
01:06:53,855 --> 01:06:57,146
You know my biggest fear, Shashank?

1071
01:06:59,396 --> 01:07:02,480
That whenever things feel perfect…

1072
01:07:02,730 --> 01:07:07,021
When it all seems to be going great,

1073
01:07:07,313 --> 01:07:09,230
you'll just break my heart and go.

1074
01:07:09,355 --> 01:07:13,105
- Why are you making this so complicated?
- I'm not complicating things.

1075
01:07:13,646 --> 01:07:15,855
I'm trying to protect myself.

1076
01:07:16,480 --> 01:07:19,646
Shashank, we need to put full stops
on some relationships,

1077
01:07:19,771 --> 01:07:22,771
so don't put a comma and drag it on.

1078
01:08:04,771 --> 01:08:05,813
Hi!

1079
01:08:06,313 --> 01:08:07,438
Hi.

1080
01:08:07,521 --> 01:08:08,980
Look what I've got.

1081
01:08:09,688 --> 01:08:11,271
Your favorite.

1082
01:08:11,938 --> 01:08:13,646
- Noodles?
- Yeah.

1083
01:08:13,771 --> 01:08:15,563
When did you start eating noodles?

1084
01:08:15,688 --> 01:08:17,063
Carbs. Wow.

1085
01:08:17,230 --> 01:08:18,980
Mine are quinoa noodles.

1086
01:08:19,896 --> 01:08:21,396
Quinoa noodles, seriously?

1087
01:08:21,480 --> 01:08:22,980
- Yuck.
- Yum.

1088
01:08:24,980 --> 01:08:26,355
What's wrong?

1089
01:08:27,396 --> 01:08:29,563
Don't ask. Work related stuff.

1090
01:08:30,563 --> 01:08:31,896
- What's up with you?
- Me?

1091
01:08:31,980 --> 01:08:33,271
I'm going to Goa.

1092
01:08:33,355 --> 01:08:34,813
What? Out of nowhere?

1093
01:08:35,313 --> 01:08:37,313
First Arjun planned it
just with his friends.

1094
01:08:37,396 --> 01:08:38,730
Now all the wives are tagging along.

1095
01:08:38,813 --> 01:08:40,563
So I'm going as well.

1096
01:08:46,646 --> 01:08:49,563
Do you even have an identity
beyond just being his wife?

1097
01:08:49,646 --> 01:08:50,563
What do you mean?

1098
01:08:50,646 --> 01:08:53,605
I mean first you did keto,

1099
01:08:53,980 --> 01:08:56,730
then the vegan phase

1100
01:08:56,896 --> 01:08:59,563
then yoga, and now this Goa trip.

1101
01:09:00,438 --> 01:09:02,563
Everything you do is just to please him.

1102
01:09:03,105 --> 01:09:04,021
No, I mean…

1103
01:09:05,396 --> 01:09:08,688
I'm... I'm happy to do it for him.

1104
01:09:12,230 --> 01:09:15,021
Naina, what kind of relationship is this?

1105
01:09:15,355 --> 01:09:16,688
This is toxic.

1106
01:09:16,813 --> 01:09:18,605
Tell me what love is.

1107
01:09:19,480 --> 01:09:20,521
Love…

1108
01:09:20,855 --> 01:09:24,188
Love means you have the freedom
to do what you want.

1109
01:09:25,063 --> 01:09:26,813
Love means honesty.

1110
01:09:28,063 --> 01:09:30,271
And you keep changing yourself for him.

1111
01:09:30,396 --> 01:09:33,105
I'm not changing myself.
That's how relationships are.

1112
01:09:33,396 --> 01:09:36,063
- What's the problem?
- The problem is…

1113
01:09:36,396 --> 01:09:38,021
Tell me something.

1114
01:09:38,105 --> 01:09:40,646
When was the last time
Arjun asked, "You okay?

1115
01:09:40,771 --> 01:09:43,105
Do you need anything? Are you happy?"

1116
01:09:44,896 --> 01:09:46,563
Has he ever asked you that?

1117
01:09:47,521 --> 01:09:50,063
When was the last time you did something

1118
01:09:50,146 --> 01:09:51,688
that made you happy?

1119
01:09:52,980 --> 01:09:54,063
Come on, tell me!

1120
01:09:57,438 --> 01:09:59,855
You wake up every morning thinking,
"What's on the menu today?

1121
01:09:59,938 --> 01:10:02,063
What nail polish color should I put on?"

1122
01:10:02,146 --> 01:10:04,730
You don't even see it,
but you're turning into mom.

1123
01:10:09,646 --> 01:10:10,896
Shit.

1124
01:10:17,688 --> 01:10:19,688
What's wrong with you these days?

1125
01:10:31,438 --> 01:10:33,563
I did everything I could, Mom,

1126
01:10:34,563 --> 01:10:36,230
but it wasn't enough.

1127
01:10:38,938 --> 01:10:41,438
It's hard being a mother, darling.

1128
01:10:43,646 --> 01:10:44,855
Just look at me…

1129
01:10:46,146 --> 01:10:48,105
I'm still taking care of you.

1130
01:11:05,313 --> 01:11:10,188
<i>What is this thing they call love?</i>

1131
01:11:10,480 --> 01:11:15,688
<i>An innocent punishment from above</i>

1132
01:11:20,563 --> 01:11:24,855
<i>What is this thing they call love?</i>

1133
01:11:25,313 --> 01:11:29,563
<i>An innocent punishment from above</i>

1134
01:11:29,646 --> 01:11:32,563
<i>The one who can't notice</i>

1135
01:11:32,771 --> 01:11:36,230
<i>The tears in my eyes</i>

1136
01:11:38,896 --> 01:11:42,938
<i>I'm upset</i>

1137
01:11:43,896 --> 01:11:47,855
<i>All my moments are filled with sorrow only</i>

1138
01:11:49,105 --> 01:11:53,063
<i>Even in the crowd</i>

1139
01:11:53,896 --> 01:11:57,396
<i>My heart feels lonely</i>

1140
01:11:57,605 --> 01:12:01,021
<i>Everywhere I go</i>

1141
01:12:01,271 --> 01:12:05,105
<i>It looks for you</i>

1142
01:12:07,313 --> 01:12:11,021
<i>With reason or without</i>

1143
01:12:11,105 --> 01:12:14,730
<i>It searches you</i>

1144
01:12:57,271 --> 01:13:01,771
<i>Stop being selfish for once</i>

1145
01:13:01,980 --> 01:13:03,980
<i>Give your mistakes</i>

1146
01:13:04,063 --> 01:13:07,313
<i>A learning chance</i>

1147
01:13:12,188 --> 01:13:16,771
<i>Stop being selfish for once</i>

1148
01:13:16,896 --> 01:13:19,313
<i>Give your mistakes</i>

1149
01:13:19,396 --> 01:13:21,771
<i>A learning chance</i>

1150
01:13:21,896 --> 01:13:24,146
<i>Do me a favor</i>

1151
01:13:24,521 --> 01:13:29,396
<i>Take my half-broken heart</i>

1152
01:13:29,563 --> 01:13:34,105
<i>Go ahead and tear it completely apart</i>

1153
01:13:35,688 --> 01:13:39,521
<i>My clouds</i>

1154
01:13:40,563 --> 01:13:44,980
<i>Have lost their every hue</i>

1155
01:13:45,271 --> 01:13:49,688
<i>And all my rains</i>

1156
01:13:50,355 --> 01:13:54,146
<i>Still belong to you</i>

1157
01:13:54,271 --> 01:13:57,730
<i>Everywhere I go</i>

1158
01:13:57,813 --> 01:14:02,480
<i>It looks for you</i>

1159
01:14:03,771 --> 01:14:07,646
<i>Needlessly, without any reason</i>

1160
01:14:07,771 --> 01:14:10,980
<i>It looks for you</i>

1161
01:14:22,521 --> 01:14:23,563
STORY OF A BROKEN HEART

1162
01:14:43,813 --> 01:14:47,896
<i>With reason or without…</i>

1163
01:15:01,230 --> 01:15:02,355
What's this?

1164
01:15:03,271 --> 01:15:05,563
You don't have to return my "t-sirt".

1165
01:15:05,771 --> 01:15:06,813
It's okay.

1166
01:15:07,396 --> 01:15:09,563
It's yours, you should keep it.

1167
01:15:11,521 --> 01:15:12,771
Really?

1168
01:15:15,688 --> 01:15:17,063
Hmm.

1169
01:15:17,896 --> 01:15:20,063
So, how are you?

1170
01:15:20,688 --> 01:15:22,688
How's life? How's work? All good?

1171
01:15:22,813 --> 01:15:24,063
All good.

1172
01:15:24,730 --> 01:15:26,021
And you?

1173
01:15:26,730 --> 01:15:28,313
What can I say?

1174
01:15:29,188 --> 01:15:31,688
I've been roaming around the mountains.

1175
01:15:32,396 --> 01:15:34,313
I saw your photos. They looked good.

1176
01:15:34,438 --> 01:15:36,105
Then why didn't you like them?

1177
01:15:36,188 --> 01:15:37,771
They weren't that great.

1178
01:15:40,313 --> 01:15:41,646
You went alone?

1179
01:15:41,896 --> 01:15:44,021
Yeah. Who else would I go with?

1180
01:15:45,646 --> 01:15:47,438
With Sonia?

1181
01:15:47,521 --> 01:15:49,271
The one you had coffee with?

1182
01:15:52,688 --> 01:15:54,730
You are feeling jealous.

1183
01:15:54,896 --> 01:15:56,188
Nice.

1184
01:15:56,271 --> 01:15:57,438
Excuse me?

1185
01:15:57,521 --> 01:15:59,771
Why would I be jealous of her?

1186
01:16:00,063 --> 01:16:01,563
No way.

1187
01:16:02,271 --> 01:16:04,771
Then why are we even talking about her?

1188
01:16:05,813 --> 01:16:08,521
You know what, Shashank?
I just came to return your t-shirt.

1189
01:16:08,605 --> 01:16:10,813
- Bye.
- "Rosni", wait…

1190
01:16:11,313 --> 01:16:12,563
I mean…

1191
01:16:14,438 --> 01:16:15,563
Bye.

1192
01:16:22,396 --> 01:16:24,688
- Call them.
- Will they get the plane tickets so soon?

1193
01:16:24,771 --> 01:16:27,521
Once they hear the good news,
they'll rush over anyway.

1194
01:16:27,605 --> 01:16:29,855
Aunt Anu, Sister Guddu,
Aunt Soma, Uncle Niraj…

1195
01:16:29,938 --> 01:16:31,730
What's up?
Why is everyone gathered in the garden?

1196
01:16:31,813 --> 01:16:34,480
- We're making arrangements.
- What for?

1197
01:16:34,563 --> 01:16:35,896
For something you did.

1198
01:16:35,980 --> 01:16:37,355
What did I do?

1199
01:16:37,605 --> 01:16:39,896
You should've told us
you wanted to marry Shashank.

1200
01:16:39,980 --> 01:16:41,730
I kept fasting
for your marriage for nothing.

1201
01:16:41,813 --> 01:16:43,688
At least we saved a ton on groceries.

1202
01:16:43,771 --> 01:16:45,980
- What nonsense!
- Stop it!

1203
01:16:46,438 --> 01:16:47,730
Did you meet Shashank?

1204
01:16:47,813 --> 01:16:49,271
Did you?

1205
01:16:49,813 --> 01:16:50,896
Yes, I did. But…

1206
01:16:50,980 --> 01:16:54,146
- Did you have coffee with him?
- Did you?

1207
01:16:54,271 --> 01:16:56,438
Yes, but it was just casual.

1208
01:16:56,563 --> 01:16:57,855
- Oh, just casual.
- I see.

1209
01:16:57,938 --> 01:16:58,896
Hold on.

1210
01:16:58,980 --> 01:16:59,855
Go on.

1211
01:16:59,980 --> 01:17:02,230
- Straight to engagement, then?
- Bittu! Password!

1212
01:17:02,313 --> 01:17:04,521
- You want to do it right away?
- 0007.

1213
01:17:05,230 --> 01:17:06,813
Mom, tell me.

1214
01:17:07,146 --> 01:17:11,563
Does this hug look casual to you?

1215
01:17:14,271 --> 01:17:16,313
Doesn't look like it.

1216
01:17:16,813 --> 01:17:17,813
Oh, this!

1217
01:17:17,938 --> 01:17:19,855
- You are overthinking. I…
- I had a word with him.

1218
01:17:19,938 --> 01:17:21,813
- Dad…
- I spoke with Shashank's dad.

1219
01:17:21,896 --> 01:17:24,313
- Okay.
- He's a good man. Really good.

1220
01:17:24,396 --> 01:17:27,063
He agreed they should get engaged
right away and marry in a month or two.

1221
01:17:27,146 --> 01:17:30,188
Amazing! You've never
worked this fast in your life.

1222
01:17:30,271 --> 01:17:32,521
That's the second time
you've complimented me.

1223
01:17:32,605 --> 01:17:34,230
- Dad…
- So happy for you, dear.

1224
01:17:34,313 --> 01:17:35,813
- So happy for you.
- High five!

1225
01:17:35,896 --> 01:17:39,105
Well, I'm worried because they want
the engagement immediately.

1226
01:17:39,188 --> 01:17:42,188
We need to sort out a lot of things.
Book the venue…

1227
01:17:42,271 --> 01:17:44,396
You should just stay stuck to the couch.

1228
01:17:44,480 --> 01:17:45,480
Don't step out.

1229
01:17:45,646 --> 01:17:46,771
What?

1230
01:17:46,896 --> 01:17:47,938
Game!

1231
01:17:49,730 --> 01:17:50,980
I'll deal with you later.

1232
01:17:55,313 --> 01:17:56,271
Shashank!

1233
01:17:56,396 --> 01:17:57,605
Hello, "Rosni"?

1234
01:17:57,688 --> 01:18:00,688
I got a call from my dad.
What did you tell your parents?

1235
01:18:00,771 --> 01:18:03,980
I didn't tell them anything.
This stupid Bittu…

1236
01:18:04,563 --> 01:18:06,438
He saw us together at the cafe.

1237
01:18:06,646 --> 01:18:07,896
Oh!

1238
01:18:08,271 --> 01:18:11,188
Bittu's going to get a whacking from me.

1239
01:18:12,188 --> 01:18:14,563
Excuse me, he's my brother.

1240
01:18:14,771 --> 01:18:16,146
I can say whatever to him,

1241
01:18:16,230 --> 01:18:18,105
but you don't get to. Got it?

1242
01:18:23,771 --> 01:18:24,813
So…

1243
01:18:26,021 --> 01:18:27,813
I… I mean…

1244
01:18:29,146 --> 01:18:30,438
What do we do now?

1245
01:18:32,896 --> 01:18:35,021
L-Let's just do it.

1246
01:18:37,646 --> 01:18:38,771
Alright.

1247
01:18:39,688 --> 01:18:41,271
Let's go for it.

1248
01:18:44,313 --> 01:18:45,688
Are you "fure"?

1249
01:18:46,646 --> 01:18:48,521
A hundred percent "fure".

1250
01:19:05,813 --> 01:19:07,563
Hi…

1251
01:19:08,146 --> 01:19:09,771
Can we reduce the music, please?

1252
01:19:10,146 --> 01:19:12,396
It's such a beautiful day.

1253
01:19:12,896 --> 01:19:15,771
I mean, today is extra special.

1254
01:19:15,896 --> 01:19:20,188
The whole family is together
after a very long time.

1255
01:19:20,646 --> 01:19:22,646
They've all known Roshni

1256
01:19:22,771 --> 01:19:25,605
since she was just a little girl.

1257
01:19:26,480 --> 01:19:29,063
So, Mr. Shashank Sharma,

1258
01:19:29,396 --> 01:19:32,396
my soon-to-be brother-in-law,

1259
01:19:32,521 --> 01:19:35,896
would you like to say a few words
about your future wife?

1260
01:19:36,063 --> 01:19:38,980
Because trust me, once you're married

1261
01:19:39,188 --> 01:19:41,313
you will hardly get to say anything.

1262
01:19:41,646 --> 01:19:43,063
Come on, please.

1263
01:19:43,313 --> 01:19:44,396
Please.

1264
01:19:44,563 --> 01:19:46,730
Come on, Shashank.
We all want to hear you.

1265
01:19:46,813 --> 01:19:47,980
Come on.

1266
01:19:48,063 --> 01:19:50,563
Brother-in-law! Brother-in-law!

1267
01:19:50,646 --> 01:19:53,355
- Brother-in-law, come on!
- Come on. Please.

1268
01:19:53,438 --> 01:19:56,438
Speak up. You won't get a chance later.

1269
01:19:56,646 --> 01:19:59,563
- Come on, Shashank.
- Speak up.

1270
01:20:00,271 --> 01:20:02,313
Come on. Please.

1271
01:20:04,480 --> 01:20:05,730
Come on.

1272
01:20:12,396 --> 01:20:14,188
- Hey!
- Who is that?

1273
01:20:16,938 --> 01:20:18,688
I'd like him to speak on my behalf.

1274
01:20:18,813 --> 01:20:21,563
Today my brother's getting engaged!

1275
01:20:22,646 --> 01:20:25,396
Who can stop me now?

1276
01:20:25,480 --> 01:20:28,188
- Give me a huge round of applause!
- He's a bit drunk.

1277
01:20:28,605 --> 01:20:30,605
- Applaud, please.
- He seems drunk.

1278
01:20:30,813 --> 01:20:34,021
Shashank's always been the underdog.

1279
01:20:36,188 --> 01:20:37,271
Why is he barking?

1280
01:20:37,355 --> 01:20:39,688
He somehow always wins in the end.

1281
01:20:39,980 --> 01:20:42,355
He is a darling.

1282
01:20:42,771 --> 01:20:46,771
When he first told me about Roshni,

1283
01:20:47,188 --> 01:20:50,938
I swear to God, that's it. Period.

1284
01:20:51,646 --> 01:20:55,188
I told him straight away
that she is the one.

1285
01:20:55,980 --> 01:20:58,938
- He said that?
- And not to let her go.

1286
01:20:59,021 --> 01:21:01,230
He's drunk, so he's rambling.

1287
01:21:01,313 --> 01:21:02,980
Shashank told me,

1288
01:21:03,188 --> 01:21:06,146
that he was in love!

1289
01:21:07,021 --> 01:21:08,313
He seriously said that.

1290
01:21:08,396 --> 01:21:09,813
He tells me everything.

1291
01:21:10,313 --> 01:21:12,271
Every single thing…

1292
01:21:12,438 --> 01:21:14,896
When they met for the first time…

1293
01:21:16,063 --> 01:21:19,271
the clouds rolled in, lightning flashed,

1294
01:21:19,563 --> 01:21:23,438
and they just stared at each other.

1295
01:21:23,646 --> 01:21:26,896
- Roshni looked into Shashank's eyes…
- Have you told him everything?

1296
01:21:26,980 --> 01:21:28,771
And she asked him

1297
01:21:28,896 --> 01:21:32,271
if he likes the rain.

1298
01:21:32,896 --> 01:21:35,021
- That's nothing, Uncle Deepak.
- Stop it!

1299
01:21:35,105 --> 01:21:36,771
The first time…

1300
01:21:37,271 --> 01:21:40,063
- Shashank…
- …when she went to his house…

1301
01:21:40,146 --> 01:21:41,521
Shashank!

1302
01:21:42,146 --> 01:21:44,688
- Should I tell them?
- Will you stop him or should I?

1303
01:21:44,771 --> 01:21:46,271
Hey!

1304
01:21:46,688 --> 01:21:48,021
It's enough.

1305
01:21:48,355 --> 01:21:49,480
Mom, that's enough.

1306
01:21:49,563 --> 01:21:50,688
