01:42:16,980 --> 01:42:18,730
You've never been in love,

1565
01:42:19,396 --> 01:42:22,938
no girlfriend, not married either…

1566
01:42:23,813 --> 01:42:27,021
So where the hell are you getting
all this great wisdom from?

1567
01:42:27,271 --> 01:42:28,688
I've got a lot of free time.

1568
01:42:28,771 --> 01:42:30,271
Write this down.

1569
01:42:30,396 --> 01:42:33,063
You'll have to go to her.
She won't come to you.

1570
01:42:33,146 --> 01:42:35,646
And if she does, then tell me.
mark my words.

1571
01:42:36,605 --> 01:42:39,063
Hey, dear! You got off work early today?

1572
01:42:39,646 --> 01:42:41,313
I took a permanent off from work.

1573
01:42:42,063 --> 01:42:43,396
I resigned.

1574
01:42:44,480 --> 01:42:45,896
- You resigned?
- You resigned?

1575
01:42:45,980 --> 01:42:47,938
Mom, not now, please.

1576
01:42:50,980 --> 01:42:53,563
- What have you done to yourself, Naina?
- Mom, where's Roshni?

1577
01:42:53,646 --> 01:42:55,896
She's in her room.
What's going on with you?

1578
01:42:55,980 --> 01:42:57,646
Mom, not now, please.

1579
01:43:00,438 --> 01:43:01,855
Not now, please.

1580
01:43:05,896 --> 01:43:06,896
Naina?

1581
01:43:08,646 --> 01:43:09,646
What's wrong?

1582
01:43:16,646 --> 01:43:19,730
The bikini body I worked so hard for?

1583
01:43:19,813 --> 01:43:22,813
I starved, did intermittent fasting,
did everything.

1584
01:43:23,271 --> 01:43:25,605
You know what Arjun told me
when we got to Goa?

1585
01:43:25,688 --> 01:43:26,605
What?

1586
01:43:27,396 --> 01:43:28,646
That I look sick.

1587
01:43:30,563 --> 01:43:33,646
That's when I realized
what the hell I was doing.

1588
01:43:35,146 --> 01:43:37,563
When I was five kilos heavier,
he called me fat.

1589
01:43:37,646 --> 01:43:40,813
When I lost the weight, he called me sick.

1590
01:43:41,396 --> 01:43:42,438
- Naina.
- I mean…

1591
01:43:44,688 --> 01:43:45,813
Seriously…

1592
01:43:46,146 --> 01:43:50,980
I can't spend my whole life
fixing those five kilos.

1593
01:43:53,646 --> 01:43:54,980
I think…

1594
01:43:55,730 --> 01:43:58,355
I've been living with a goal

1595
01:43:59,563 --> 01:44:02,896
to make Arjun like me.

1596
01:44:05,063 --> 01:44:06,396
That's it.

1597
01:44:08,021 --> 01:44:09,271
But you know what?

1598
01:44:10,563 --> 01:44:12,021
No matter what I do,

1599
01:44:12,980 --> 01:44:15,105
I'm never good enough for him.

1600
01:44:15,688 --> 01:44:17,313
Never enough.

1601
01:44:19,188 --> 01:44:22,730
I can't even remember
the last time I ate till I was full.

1602
01:44:23,563 --> 01:44:24,646
Naina…

1603
01:44:27,605 --> 01:44:28,646
Come on…

1604
01:44:31,396 --> 01:44:33,563
Sugarless teas,

1605
01:44:33,688 --> 01:44:37,646
millet bread, obsessing over the scale,

1606
01:44:37,771 --> 01:44:42,146
counting fats, carbohydrates
and what not…

1607
01:44:42,271 --> 01:44:44,646
I'm losing my mind, Rosh.

1608
01:44:45,396 --> 01:44:46,896
I'm exhausted.

1609
01:44:47,396 --> 01:44:50,271
I can't live like this anymore.

1610
01:44:51,980 --> 01:44:55,646
No. I can't live like this.

1611
01:45:03,063 --> 01:45:04,563
He doesn't care.

1612
01:45:05,938 --> 01:45:07,188
Enough is enough.

1613
01:45:08,188 --> 01:45:09,646
You were right.

1614
01:45:10,771 --> 01:45:14,021
I kept changing myself for Arjun.

1615
01:45:17,563 --> 01:45:19,646
I didn't even realize it.

1616
01:45:20,980 --> 01:45:22,480
I don't even know…

1617
01:45:24,521 --> 01:45:25,813
who I am!

1618
01:45:27,771 --> 01:45:29,146
What do I like?

1619
01:45:32,271 --> 01:45:34,355
I don't know myself anymore.

1620
01:45:36,896 --> 01:45:39,396
I just don't know anything anymore.

1621
01:45:48,646 --> 01:45:49,896
But I'm happy…

1622
01:45:51,688 --> 01:45:53,688
that you've got Shashank in your life.

1623
01:45:55,563 --> 01:45:57,646
People like him are rare, Rosh.

1624
01:45:58,646 --> 01:46:00,438
It's very precious.

1625
01:46:01,771 --> 01:46:02,688
The way you are…

1626
01:46:02,771 --> 01:46:05,896
With your loose t-shirts,
and flip-flops…

1627
01:46:06,771 --> 01:46:09,188
He loves you exactly the way you are.

1628
01:46:10,605 --> 01:46:11,646
Protect it.

1629
01:46:12,480 --> 01:46:13,980
Don't ever let him go.

1630
01:46:22,813 --> 01:46:24,063
You were right.

1631
01:46:24,646 --> 01:46:26,438
I was a fool.

1632
01:46:31,313 --> 01:46:33,188
I was talking rubbish.

1633
01:46:52,146 --> 01:46:54,271
I asked the lady,

1634
01:46:55,605 --> 01:46:57,521
what that tomato dish was.

1635
01:46:58,146 --> 01:46:59,563
You…

1636
01:47:02,938 --> 01:47:05,271
It's your house,
you should answer the doorbell.

1637
01:47:14,480 --> 01:47:15,480
I'm coming!

1638
01:47:20,396 --> 01:47:21,980
There's no peace in my life.

1639
01:47:22,063 --> 01:47:24,105
The bells keep ringing all day.
Who is it?

1640
01:47:24,188 --> 01:47:25,521
This isn't your father's…

1641
01:47:39,396 --> 01:47:40,313
"Rosni."

1642
01:47:46,938 --> 01:47:48,271
I told him so!

1643
01:47:54,188 --> 01:47:55,271
I love you.

1644
01:47:58,271 --> 01:48:00,771
I-I love you too.

1645
01:48:05,271 --> 01:48:09,605
Shashank, when I was 15,

1646
01:48:10,438 --> 01:48:13,605
I went to my cousin's wedding
in Chandigarh.

1647
01:48:13,688 --> 01:48:15,771
I wore a pink lehenga.

1648
01:48:18,188 --> 01:48:20,313
My aunt said, "Look,

1649
01:48:21,605 --> 01:48:24,438
Roshni's smile is just like her mother's."

1650
01:48:25,396 --> 01:48:27,396
And you know what my mom said?

1651
01:48:29,188 --> 01:48:32,063
"But she's got her father's nose.

1652
01:48:33,063 --> 01:48:35,146
Naina is my carbon copy."

1653
