Sir, ID please.

1820
02:01:30,730 --> 02:01:32,980
- Actually, I forgot it.
- Sir?

1821
02:01:33,063 --> 02:01:35,521
Sorry, sir, no entry without an ID card.

1822
02:01:36,896 --> 02:01:38,480
My name's on the list.

1823
02:01:38,605 --> 02:01:40,438
Come with me, let's check.

1824
02:01:41,480 --> 02:01:42,521
What's your name?

1825
02:01:42,605 --> 02:01:43,980
Where did he go? Catch him!

1826
02:01:44,063 --> 02:01:46,563
Hello, ladies and gentlemen.

1827
02:01:46,646 --> 02:01:48,605
<i>Hello. I'd like to extend a warm welcome</i>

1828
02:01:48,688 --> 02:01:51,480
<i>to all the distinguished guests</i>

1829
02:01:51,563 --> 02:01:54,855
<i>and attendees present here today.</i>

1830
02:02:30,063 --> 02:02:31,438
Good morning, everyone.

1831
02:02:31,896 --> 02:02:32,896
I'm…

1832
02:02:35,188 --> 02:02:36,855
I'm "Sasank Sarma".

1833
02:02:38,563 --> 02:02:40,021
I've got a problem.

1834
02:02:41,271 --> 02:02:44,730
I pronounce 'sh' as 's',

1835
02:02:45,063 --> 02:02:48,896
and because of the worry
that I might mispronounce "attension"

1836
02:02:48,980 --> 02:02:51,521
I spent my entire life in "hesitasion".

1837
02:02:53,146 --> 02:02:56,313
But today, in my dreams,
I met seven-year-old "Sasank".

1838
02:02:56,605 --> 02:03:00,105
The "Sasank" who lived
without uncertainty, without fear.

1839
02:03:01,396 --> 02:03:03,980
I felt as if he was asking me,

1840
02:03:05,146 --> 02:03:07,146
what has happened

1841
02:03:07,771 --> 02:03:09,396
and why I'm so scared.

1842
02:03:09,771 --> 02:03:12,396
Actually, honestly, I don't even know.

1843
02:03:13,188 --> 02:03:15,188
Maybe it's because I grew up.

1844
02:03:15,605 --> 02:03:18,313
I got this fear of what people think,

1845
02:03:19,063 --> 02:03:20,646
what they'll say…

1846
02:03:21,896 --> 02:03:23,896
Am I doing it right?

1847
02:03:24,396 --> 02:03:26,480
Is my hair okay?

1848
02:03:26,813 --> 02:03:28,063
Is my tie okay?

1849
02:03:30,896 --> 02:03:32,938
What about my "pronunciason"?

1850
02:03:34,938 --> 02:03:36,396
Where do I come from?

1851
02:03:36,980 --> 02:03:38,105
What do I think?

1852
02:03:38,938 --> 02:03:40,563
Can I dream?

1853
02:03:40,813 --> 02:03:41,896
Can I dream big?

1854
02:03:43,646 --> 02:03:44,771
I was scared.

1855
02:03:48,605 --> 02:03:49,730
But not anymore.

1856
02:03:51,771 --> 02:03:55,813
I want to thank the young "Sasank"

1857
02:03:56,063 --> 02:03:57,938
for helping me face my fears.

1858
02:04:04,021 --> 02:04:05,646
So today, I've decided

1859
02:04:06,563 --> 02:04:08,896
that I will speak freely.

1860
02:04:33,230 --> 02:04:35,688
So, ladies and gentlemen,

1861
02:04:35,771 --> 02:04:37,396
can we proceed?

1862
02:04:37,688 --> 02:04:39,688
So, here we begin.

1863
02:04:41,063 --> 02:04:44,188
A company is an "instituson"
founded on trust and "devoson".

1864
02:04:44,771 --> 02:04:48,271
The workers of a company determine
the strength and "potensial" of it.

1865
02:04:48,563 --> 02:04:50,271
I've been working here
for the last five years,

1866
02:04:50,355 --> 02:04:53,271
and I've been so fortunate
to be working with the most amazing team.

1867
02:04:53,355 --> 02:04:55,271
Trust through transparency,

1868
02:04:55,396 --> 02:04:57,063
the "distribusion" of sales…

1869
02:05:03,563 --> 02:05:07,230
Expanding into the rural areas.
E-commerce with a rural twist.

1870
02:05:09,480 --> 02:05:10,730
…of our "wasing" machine.

1871
02:05:10,813 --> 02:05:12,771
Trust through transparency.

1872
02:05:13,396 --> 02:05:14,396
That's it.

1873
02:05:14,938 --> 02:05:16,146
Thank you.

1874
02:05:41,605 --> 02:05:43,188
I told you he's an underdog,

1875
02:05:43,271 --> 02:05:44,646
- but always wins in the end.
- Yes!

1876
02:05:44,730 --> 02:05:46,480
That's a sixer, right out of the ground!

1877
02:05:46,563 --> 02:05:49,355
I deleted your resignation email
without even reading it.

1878
02:05:49,646 --> 02:05:50,688
It's done.

1879
02:05:50,813 --> 02:05:54,563
- He did everything on his own.
- Yes.

1880
02:05:55,980 --> 02:05:58,855
Anil, make sure everyone is taken care of…

1881
02:06:04,188 --> 02:06:06,396
I'm so proud of you, Shashank.

1882
02:06:10,230 --> 02:06:12,355
- "Rosni" Shrivastav…
- Yes?

1883
02:06:13,230 --> 02:06:14,771
I, "Sasank Sarma",

1884
02:06:15,188 --> 02:06:17,938
in my right mind,
want to ask you something.

1885
02:06:19,021 --> 02:06:20,063
Go ahead.

1886
02:06:22,563 --> 02:06:24,146
Will you marry me?

1887
02:06:26,605 --> 02:06:27,980
Of course!

1888
02:06:33,271 --> 02:06:34,396
I love you.

1889
02:06:35,771 --> 02:06:37,146
I love you too.

1890
02:07:44,271 --> 02:07:46,188
Well, did you like the "Decorasion"?

1891
02:07:46,271 --> 02:07:49,313
I love it! It's great!

1892
02:07:52,396 --> 02:07:53,938
What is this, Shashank?

1893
02:07:56,688 --> 02:07:58,896
I told them to write "Rosni weds Sasank",

1894
02:07:58,980 --> 02:08:01,480
and those idiots
wrote "Rosni weds Sasank" instead!

1895
02:08:01,730 --> 02:08:03,146
What?

